7407  SDValue Dividend = DAG.getNode(ISD::BUILD_PAIR, dl, VT, LL, LH);
7408  SDValue Rem = DAG.getNode(ISD::BUILD_PAIR, dl, VT, RemL, RemH);
7409 
7410  Dividend = DAG.getNode(ISD::SUB, dl, VT, Dividend, Rem);
7411 
7412  // Multiply by the multiplicative inverse of the divisor modulo
7413  // (1 << BitWidth).
7414  APInt Mod = APInt::getSignedMinValue(BitWidth + 1);
7415  APInt MulFactor = Divisor.zext(BitWidth + 1);
7416  MulFactor = MulFactor.multiplicativeInverse(Mod);
7417  MulFactor = MulFactor.trunc(BitWidth);
7418 
7419  SDValue Quotient = DAG.getNode(ISD::MUL, dl, VT, Dividend,
7420  DAG.getConstant(MulFactor, dl, VT));
7421 
7422  // Split the quotient into low and high parts.
7423  SDValue QuotL = DAG.getNode(ISD::EXTRACT_ELEMENT, dl, HiLoVT, Quotient,
7424  DAG.getIntPtrConstant(0, dl));
7425  SDValue QuotH = DAG.getNode(ISD::EXTRACT_ELEMENT, dl, HiLoVT, Quotient,
7426  DAG.getIntPtrConstant(1, dl));
7427  Result.push_back(QuotL);
7428  Result.push_back(QuotH);
7429  }
7430 
7431  if (Opcode != ISD::UDIV) {
7432  // If we shifted the input, shift the remainder left and add the bits we
7433  // shifted off the input.
7434  if (TrailingZeros) {
7435  APInt Mask = APInt::getLowBitsSet(HBitWidth, TrailingZeros);
7436  RemL = DAG.getNode(ISD::SHL, dl, HiLoVT, RemL,
7437  DAG.getShiftAmountConstant(TrailingZeros, HiLoVT, dl));
7438  RemL = DAG.getNode(ISD::ADD, dl, HiLoVT, RemL, PartialRem);
7439  }
7440  Result.push_back(RemL);
7441  Result.push_back(DAG.getConstant(0, dl, HiLoVT));
7442  }
7443 
7444  return true;
7445 }
7446 
7447 // Check that (every element of) Z is undef or not an exact multiple of BW.
7448 static bool isNonZeroModBitWidthOrUndef(SDValue Z, unsigned BW) {
7449  return ISD::matchUnaryPredicate(
7450  Z,
7451  [=](ConstantSDNode *C) { return !C || C->getAPIntValue().urem(BW) != 0; },
7452  true);
7453 }
7454 
7455 static SDValue expandVPFunnelShift(SDNode *Node, SelectionDAG &DAG) {
7456  EVT VT = Node->getValueType(0);
7457  SDValue ShX, ShY;
7458  SDValue ShAmt, InvShAmt;
7459  SDValue X = Node->getOperand(0);
7460  SDValue Y = Node->getOperand(1);
7461  SDValue Z = Node->getOperand(2);
7462  SDValue Mask = Node->getOperand(3);
7463  SDValue VL = Node->getOperand(4);
7464 
7465  unsigned BW = VT.getScalarSizeInBits();
7466  bool IsFSHL = Node->getOpcode() == ISD::VP_FSHL;
7467  SDLoc DL(SDValue(Node, 0));
7468 
7469  EVT ShVT = Z.getValueType();
7470  if (isNonZeroModBitWidthOrUndef(Z, BW)) {
7471  // fshl: X << C | Y >> (BW - C)
7472  // fshr: X << (BW - C) | Y >> C
7473  // where C = Z % BW is not zero
7474  SDValue BitWidthC = DAG.getConstant(BW, DL, ShVT);
7475  ShAmt = DAG.getNode(ISD::VP_UREM, DL, ShVT, Z, BitWidthC, Mask, VL);
7476  InvShAmt = DAG.getNode(ISD::VP_SUB, DL, ShVT, BitWidthC, ShAmt, Mask, VL);
7477  ShX = DAG.getNode(ISD::VP_SHL, DL, VT, X, IsFSHL ? ShAmt : InvShAmt, Mask,
7478  VL);
7479  ShY = DAG.getNode(ISD::VP_LSHR, DL, VT, Y, IsFSHL ? InvShAmt : ShAmt, Mask,
7480  VL);
7481  } else {
7482  // fshl: X << (Z % BW) | Y >> 1 >> (BW - 1 - (Z % BW))
7483  // fshr: X << 1 << (BW - 1 - (Z % BW)) | Y >> (Z % BW)
7484  SDValue BitMask = DAG.getConstant(BW - 1, DL, ShVT);
7485  if (isPowerOf2_32(BW)) {
7486  // Z % BW -> Z & (BW - 1)
7487  ShAmt = DAG.getNode(ISD::VP_AND, DL, ShVT, Z, BitMask, Mask, VL);
7488  // (BW - 1) - (Z % BW) -> ~Z & (BW - 1)
7489  SDValue NotZ = DAG.getNode(ISD::VP_XOR, DL, ShVT, Z,
7490  DAG.getAllOnesConstant(DL, ShVT), Mask, VL);
7491  InvShAmt = DAG.getNode(ISD::VP_AND, DL, ShVT, NotZ, BitMask, Mask, VL);
7492  } else {
7493  SDValue BitWidthC = DAG.getConstant(BW, DL, ShVT);
7494  ShAmt = DAG.getNode(ISD::VP_UREM, DL, ShVT, Z, BitWidthC, Mask, VL);
7495  InvShAmt = DAG.getNode(ISD::VP_SUB, DL, ShVT, BitMask, ShAmt, Mask, VL);
7496  }
7497 
7498  SDValue One = DAG.getConstant(1, DL, ShVT);
7499  if (IsFSHL) {
7500  ShX = DAG.getNode(ISD::VP_SHL, DL, VT, X, ShAmt, Mask, VL);
7501  SDValue ShY1 = DAG.getNode(ISD::VP_LSHR, DL, VT, Y, One, Mask, VL);
7502  ShY = DAG.getNode(ISD::VP_LSHR, DL, VT, ShY1, InvShAmt, Mask, VL);
7503  } else {
7504  SDValue ShX1 = DAG.getNode(ISD::VP_SHL, DL, VT, X, One, Mask, VL);
7505  ShX = DAG.getNode(ISD::VP_SHL, DL, VT, ShX1, InvShAmt, Mask, VL);
7506  ShY = DAG.getNode(ISD::VP_LSHR, DL, VT, Y, ShAmt, Mask, VL);
7507  }
7508  }
7509  return DAG.getNode(ISD::VP_OR, DL, VT, ShX, ShY, Mask, VL);
7510 }
7511 
7512 SDValue TargetLowering::expandFunnelShift(SDNode *Node,
7513  SelectionDAG &DAG) const {
7514  if (Node->isVPOpcode())
7515  return expandVPFunnelShift(Node, DAG);
7516 
7517  EVT VT = Node->getValueType(0);
7518 
7519  if (VT.isVector() && (!isOperationLegalOrCustom(ISD::SHL, VT) ||
7520  !isOperationLegalOrCustom(ISD::SRL, VT) ||
7521  !isOperationLegalOrCustom(ISD::SUB, VT) ||
7522  !isOperationLegalOrCustomOrPromote(ISD::OR, VT)))
7523  return SDValue();
7524 
7525  SDValue X = Node->getOperand(0);
7526  SDValue Y = Node->getOperand(1);
7527  SDValue Z = Node->getOperand(2);
7528 
7529  unsigned BW = VT.getScalarSizeInBits();
7530  bool IsFSHL = Node->getOpcode() == ISD::FSHL;
7531  SDLoc DL(SDValue(Node, 0));
7532 
7533  EVT ShVT = Z.getValueType();
7534 
7535  // If a funnel shift in the other direction is more supported, use it.
7536  unsigned RevOpcode = IsFSHL ? ISD::FSHR : ISD::FSHL;
7537  if (!isOperationLegalOrCustom(Node->getOpcode(), VT) &&
7538  isOperationLegalOrCustom(RevOpcode, VT) && isPowerOf2_32(BW)) {
7539  if (isNonZeroModBitWidthOrUndef(Z, BW)) {
7540  // fshl X, Y, Z -> fshr X, Y, -Z
7541  // fshr X, Y, Z -> fshl X, Y, -Z
7542  SDValue Zero = DAG.getConstant(0, DL, ShVT);
7543  Z = DAG.getNode(ISD::SUB, DL, VT, Zero, Z);
7544  } else {
7545  // fshl X, Y, Z -> fshr (srl X, 1), (fshr X, Y, 1), ~Z
7546  // fshr X, Y, Z -> fshl (fshl X, Y, 1), (shl Y, 1), ~Z
7547  SDValue One = DAG.getConstant(1, DL, ShVT);
7548  if (IsFSHL) {
7549  Y = DAG.getNode(RevOpcode, DL, VT, X, Y, One);
7550  X = DAG.getNode(ISD::SRL, DL, VT, X, One);
7551  } else {
7552  X = DAG.getNode(RevOpcode, DL, VT, X, Y, One);
7553  Y = DAG.getNode(ISD::SHL, DL, VT, Y, One);
7554  }
7555  Z = DAG.getNOT(DL, Z, ShVT);
7556  }
7557  return DAG.getNode(RevOpcode, DL, VT, X, Y, Z);
7558  }
7559 
7560  SDValue ShX, ShY;
7561  SDValue ShAmt, InvShAmt;
7562  if (isNonZeroModBitWidthOrUndef(Z, BW)) {
7563  // fshl: X << C | Y >> (BW - C)
7564  // fshr: X << (BW - C) | Y >> C
7565  // where C = Z % BW is not zero
7566  SDValue BitWidthC = DAG.getConstant(BW, DL, ShVT);
7567  ShAmt = DAG.getNode(ISD::UREM, DL, ShVT, Z, BitWidthC);
7568  InvShAmt = DAG.getNode(ISD::SUB, DL, ShVT, BitWidthC, ShAmt);
7569  ShX = DAG.getNode(ISD::SHL, DL, VT, X, IsFSHL ? ShAmt : InvShAmt);
7570  ShY = DAG.getNode(ISD::SRL, DL, VT, Y, IsFSHL ? InvShAmt : ShAmt);
7571  } else {
7572  // fshl: X << (Z % BW) | Y >> 1 >> (BW - 1 - (Z % BW))
7573  // fshr: X << 1 << (BW - 1 - (Z % BW)) | Y >> (Z % BW)
7574  SDValue Mask = DAG.getConstant(BW - 1, DL, ShVT);
7575  if (isPowerOf2_32(BW)) {
7576  // Z % BW -> Z & (BW - 1)
7577  ShAmt = DAG.getNode(ISD::AND, DL, ShVT, Z, Mask);
7578  // (BW - 1) - (Z % BW) -> ~Z & (BW - 1)
7579  InvShAmt = DAG.getNode(ISD::AND, DL, ShVT, DAG.getNOT(DL, Z, ShVT), Mask);
7580  } else {
7581  SDValue BitWidthC = DAG.getConstant(BW, DL, ShVT);
7582  ShAmt = DAG.getNode(ISD::UREM, DL, ShVT, Z, BitWidthC);
7583  InvShAmt = DAG.getNode(ISD::SUB, DL, ShVT, Mask, ShAmt);
7584  }
7585 
7586  SDValue One = DAG.getConstant(1, DL, ShVT);
7587  if (IsFSHL) {
7588  ShX = DAG.getNode(ISD::SHL, DL, VT, X, ShAmt);
7589  SDValue ShY1 = DAG.getNode(ISD::SRL, DL, VT, Y, One);
7590  ShY = DAG.getNode(ISD::SRL, DL, VT, ShY1, InvShAmt);
7591  } else {
7592  SDValue ShX1 = DAG.getNode(ISD::SHL, DL, VT, X, One);
7593  ShX = DAG.getNode(ISD::SHL, DL, VT, ShX1, InvShAmt);
7594  ShY = DAG.getNode(ISD::SRL, DL, VT, Y, ShAmt);
7595  }
7596  }
7597  return DAG.getNode(ISD::OR, DL, VT, ShX, ShY);
7598 }
7599 
7600 // TODO: Merge with expandFunnelShift.
7601 SDValue TargetLowering::expandROT(SDNode *Node, bool AllowVectorOps,
7602  SelectionDAG &DAG) const {
7603  EVT VT = Node->getValueType(0);
7604  unsigned EltSizeInBits = VT.getScalarSizeInBits();
7605  bool IsLeft = Node->getOpcode() == ISD::ROTL;
7606  SDValue Op0 = Node->getOperand(0);
7607  SDValue Op1 = Node->getOperand(1);
7608  SDLoc DL(SDValue(Node, 0));
7609 
7610  EVT ShVT = Op1.getValueType();
7611  SDValue Zero = DAG.getConstant(0, DL, ShVT);
7612 
7613  // If a rotate in the other direction is more supported, use it.
7614  unsigned RevRot = IsLeft ? ISD::ROTR : ISD::ROTL;
7615  if (!isOperationLegalOrCustom(Node->getOpcode(), VT) &&
7616  isOperationLegalOrCustom(RevRot, VT) && isPowerOf2_32(EltSizeInBits)) {
7617  SDValue Sub = DAG.getNode(ISD::SUB, DL, ShVT, Zero, Op1);
7618  return DAG.getNode(RevRot, DL, VT, Op0, Sub);
7619  }
7620 
7621  if (!AllowVectorOps && VT.isVector() &&
7622  (!isOperationLegalOrCustom(ISD::SHL, VT) ||
7623  !isOperationLegalOrCustom(ISD::SRL, VT) ||
7624  !isOperationLegalOrCustom(ISD::SUB, VT) ||
7625  !isOperationLegalOrCustomOrPromote(ISD::OR, VT) ||
7626  !isOperationLegalOrCustomOrPromote(ISD::AND, VT)))
7627  return SDValue();
7628 
7629  unsigned ShOpc = IsLeft ? ISD::SHL : ISD::SRL;
7630  unsigned HsOpc = IsLeft ? ISD::SRL : ISD::SHL;
7631  SDValue BitWidthMinusOneC = DAG.getConstant(EltSizeInBits - 1, DL, ShVT);
7632  SDValue ShVal;
7633  SDValue HsVal;
7634  if (isPowerOf2_32(EltSizeInBits)) {
7635  // (rotl x, c) -> x << (c & (w - 1)) | x >> (-c & (w - 1))
7636  // (rotr x, c) -> x >> (c & (w - 1)) | x << (-c & (w - 1))
7637  SDValue NegOp1 = DAG.getNode(ISD::SUB, DL, ShVT, Zero, Op1);
7638  SDValue ShAmt = DAG.getNode(ISD::AND, DL, ShVT, Op1, BitWidthMinusOneC);
7639  ShVal = DAG.getNode(ShOpc, DL, VT, Op0, ShAmt);
7640  SDValue HsAmt = DAG.getNode(ISD::AND, DL, ShVT, NegOp1, BitWidthMinusOneC);
7641  HsVal = DAG.getNode(HsOpc, DL, VT, Op0, HsAmt);
7642  } else {
7643  // (rotl x, c) -> x << (c % w) | x >> 1 >> (w - 1 - (c % w))
7644  // (rotr x, c) -> x >> (c % w) | x << 1 << (w - 1 - (c % w))
7645  SDValue BitWidthC = DAG.getConstant(EltSizeInBits, DL, ShVT);
7646  SDValue ShAmt = DAG.getNode(ISD::UREM, DL, ShVT, Op1, BitWidthC);
7647  ShVal = DAG.getNode(ShOpc, DL, VT, Op0, ShAmt);
7648  SDValue HsAmt = DAG.getNode(ISD::SUB, DL, ShVT, BitWidthMinusOneC, ShAmt);
7649  SDValue One = DAG.getConstant(1, DL, ShVT);
7650  HsVal =
7651  DAG.getNode(HsOpc, DL, VT, DAG.getNode(HsOpc, DL, VT, Op0, One), HsAmt);
7652  }
7653  return DAG.getNode(ISD::OR, DL, VT, ShVal, HsVal);
7654 }
7655 
7656 void TargetLowering::expandShiftParts(SDNode *Node, SDValue &Lo, SDValue &Hi,
7657  SelectionDAG &DAG) const {
7658  assert(Node->getNumOperands() == 3 && "Not a double-shift!");
7659  EVT VT = Node->getValueType(0);
7660  unsigned VTBits = VT.getScalarSizeInBits();
7661  assert(isPowerOf2_32(VTBits) && "Power-of-two integer type expected");
7662 
7663  bool IsSHL = Node->getOpcode() == ISD::SHL_PARTS;
7664  bool IsSRA = Node->getOpcode() == ISD::SRA_PARTS;
7665  SDValue ShOpLo = Node->getOperand(0);
7666  SDValue ShOpHi = Node->getOperand(1);
7667  SDValue ShAmt = Node->getOperand(2);
7668  EVT ShAmtVT = ShAmt.getValueType();
7669  EVT ShAmtCCVT =
7670  getSetCCResultType(DAG.getDataLayout(), *DAG.getContext(), ShAmtVT);
7671  SDLoc dl(Node);
7672 
7673  // ISD::FSHL and ISD::FSHR have defined overflow behavior but ISD::SHL and
7674  // ISD::SRA/L nodes haven't. Insert an AND to be safe, it's usually optimized
7675  // away during isel.
7676  SDValue SafeShAmt = DAG.getNode(ISD::AND, dl, ShAmtVT, ShAmt,
7677  DAG.getConstant(VTBits - 1, dl, ShAmtVT));
7678  SDValue Tmp1 = IsSRA ? DAG.getNode(ISD::SRA, dl, VT, ShOpHi,
7679  DAG.getConstant(VTBits - 1, dl, ShAmtVT))
7680  : DAG.getConstant(0, dl, VT);
7681 
7682  SDValue Tmp2, Tmp3;
7683  if (IsSHL) {
7684  Tmp2 = DAG.getNode(ISD::FSHL, dl, VT, ShOpHi, ShOpLo, ShAmt);
7685  Tmp3 = DAG.getNode(ISD::SHL, dl, VT, ShOpLo, SafeShAmt);
7686  } else {
7687  Tmp2 = DAG.getNode(ISD::FSHR, dl, VT, ShOpHi, ShOpLo, ShAmt);
7688  Tmp3 = DAG.getNode(IsSRA ? ISD::SRA : ISD::SRL, dl, VT, ShOpHi, SafeShAmt);
7689  }
7690 
7691  // If the shift amount is larger or equal than the width of a part we don't
7692  // use the result from the FSHL/FSHR. Insert a test and select the appropriate
7693  // values for large shift amounts.
7694  SDValue AndNode = DAG.getNode(ISD::AND, dl, ShAmtVT, ShAmt,
7695  DAG.getConstant(VTBits, dl, ShAmtVT));
7696  SDValue Cond = DAG.getSetCC(dl, ShAmtCCVT, AndNode,
7697  DAG.getConstant(0, dl, ShAmtVT), ISD::SETNE);
7698 
7699  if (IsSHL) {
7700  Hi = DAG.getNode(ISD::SELECT, dl, VT, Cond, Tmp3, Tmp2);
7701  Lo = DAG.getNode(ISD::SELECT, dl, VT, Cond, Tmp1, Tmp3);
7702  } else {
7703  Lo = DAG.getNode(ISD::SELECT, dl, VT, Cond, Tmp3, Tmp2);
7704  Hi = DAG.getNode(ISD::SELECT, dl, VT, Cond, Tmp1, Tmp3);
7705  }
7706 }
7707 
7708 bool TargetLowering::expandFP_TO_SINT(SDNode *Node, SDValue &Result,
7709  SelectionDAG &DAG) const {
7710  unsigned OpNo = Node->isStrictFPOpcode() ? 1 : 0;
7711  SDValue Src = Node->getOperand(OpNo);
7712  EVT SrcVT = Src.getValueType();
7713  EVT DstVT = Node->getValueType(0);
7714  SDLoc dl(SDValue(Node, 0));
7715 
7716  // FIXME: Only f32 to i64 conversions are supported.
7717  if (SrcVT != MVT::f32 || DstVT != MVT::i64)
7718  return false;
7719 
7720  if (Node->isStrictFPOpcode())
7721  // When a NaN is converted to an integer a trap is allowed. We can't
7722  // use this expansion here because it would eliminate that trap. Other
7723  // traps are also allowed and cannot be eliminated. See
7724  // IEEE 754-2008 sec 5.8.
7725  return false;
7726 
7727  // Expand f32 -> i64 conversion
7728  // This algorithm comes from compiler-rt's implementation of fixsfdi:
7729  // https://github.com/llvm/llvm-project/blob/main/compiler-rt/lib/builtins/fixsfdi.c
7730  unsigned SrcEltBits = SrcVT.getScalarSizeInBits();
7731  EVT IntVT = SrcVT.changeTypeToInteger();
7732  EVT IntShVT = getShiftAmountTy(IntVT, DAG.getDataLayout());
7733 
7734  SDValue ExponentMask = DAG.getConstant(0x7F800000, dl, IntVT);
7735  SDValue ExponentLoBit = DAG.getConstant(23, dl, IntVT);
7736  SDValue Bias = DAG.getConstant(127, dl, IntVT);
7737  SDValue SignMask = DAG.getConstant(APInt::getSignMask(SrcEltBits), dl, IntVT);
7738  SDValue SignLowBit = DAG.getConstant(SrcEltBits - 1, dl, IntVT);
7739  SDValue MantissaMask = DAG.getConstant(0x007FFFFF, dl, IntVT);
7740 
7741  SDValue Bits = DAG.getNode(ISD::BITCAST, dl, IntVT, Src);
7742 
7743  SDValue ExponentBits = DAG.getNode(
7744  ISD::SRL, dl, IntVT, DAG.getNode(ISD::AND, dl, IntVT, Bits, ExponentMask),
7745  DAG.getZExtOrTrunc(ExponentLoBit, dl, IntShVT));
7746  SDValue Exponent = DAG.getNode(ISD::SUB, dl, IntVT, ExponentBits, Bias);
7747 
7748  SDValue Sign = DAG.getNode(ISD::SRA, dl, IntVT,
7749  DAG.getNode(ISD::AND, dl, IntVT, Bits, SignMask),
7750  DAG.getZExtOrTrunc(SignLowBit, dl, IntShVT));
7751  Sign = DAG.getSExtOrTrunc(Sign, dl, DstVT);
7752 
7753  SDValue R = DAG.getNode(ISD::OR, dl, IntVT,
7754  DAG.getNode(ISD::AND, dl, IntVT, Bits, MantissaMask),
7755  DAG.getConstant(0x00800000, dl, IntVT));
7756 
7757  R = DAG.getZExtOrTrunc(R, dl, DstVT);
7758 
7759  R = DAG.getSelectCC(
7760  dl, Exponent, ExponentLoBit,
7761  DAG.getNode(ISD::SHL, dl, DstVT, R,
7762  DAG.getZExtOrTrunc(
7763  DAG.getNode(ISD::SUB, dl, IntVT, Exponent, ExponentLoBit),
7764  dl, IntShVT)),
7765  DAG.getNode(ISD::SRL, dl, DstVT, R,
7766  DAG.getZExtOrTrunc(
7767  DAG.getNode(ISD::SUB, dl, IntVT, ExponentLoBit, Exponent),
7768  dl, IntShVT)),
7769  ISD::SETGT);
7770 
7771  SDValue Ret = DAG.getNode(ISD::SUB, dl, DstVT,
7772  DAG.getNode(ISD::XOR, dl, DstVT, R, Sign), Sign);
7773 
7774  Result = DAG.getSelectCC(dl, Exponent, DAG.getConstant(0, dl, IntVT),
7775  DAG.getConstant(0, dl, DstVT), Ret, ISD::SETLT);
7776  return true;
7777 }
7778 
7779 bool TargetLowering::expandFP_TO_UINT(SDNode *Node, SDValue &Result,
7780  SDValue &Chain,
7781  SelectionDAG &DAG) const {
7782  SDLoc dl(SDValue(Node, 0));
7783  unsigned OpNo = Node->isStrictFPOpcode() ? 1 : 0;
7784  SDValue Src = Node->getOperand(OpNo);
7785 
7786  EVT SrcVT = Src.getValueType();
7787  EVT DstVT = Node->getValueType(0);
7788  EVT SetCCVT =
7789  getSetCCResultType(DAG.getDataLayout(), *DAG.getContext(), SrcVT);
7790  EVT DstSetCCVT =
7791  getSetCCResultType(DAG.getDataLayout(), *DAG.getContext(), DstVT);
7792 
7793  // Only expand vector types if we have the appropriate vector bit operations.
7794  unsigned SIntOpcode = Node->isStrictFPOpcode() ? ISD::STRICT_FP_TO_SINT :
7795  ISD::FP_TO_SINT;
7796  if (DstVT.isVector() && (!isOperationLegalOrCustom(SIntOpcode, DstVT) ||
7797  !isOperationLegalOrCustomOrPromote(ISD::XOR, SrcVT)))
7798  return false;
7799 
7800  // If the maximum float value is smaller then the signed integer range,
7801  // the destination signmask can't be represented by the float, so we can
7802  // just use FP_TO_SINT directly.
7803  const fltSemantics &APFSem = DAG.EVTToAPFloatSemantics(SrcVT);
7804  APFloat APF(APFSem, APInt::getZero(SrcVT.getScalarSizeInBits()));
7805  APInt SignMask = APInt::getSignMask(DstVT.getScalarSizeInBits());
7806  if (APFloat::opOverflow &
7807  APF.convertFromAPInt(SignMask, false, APFloat::rmNearestTiesToEven)) {
7808  if (Node->isStrictFPOpcode()) {
7809  Result = DAG.getNode(ISD::STRICT_FP_TO_SINT, dl, { DstVT, MVT::Other },
7810  { Node->getOperand(0), Src });
7811  Chain = Result.getValue(1);
7812  } else
7813  Result = DAG.getNode(ISD::FP_TO_SINT, dl, DstVT, Src);
7814  return true;
7815  }
7816 
7817  // Don't expand it if there isn't cheap fsub instruction.
7818  if (!isOperationLegalOrCustom(
7819  Node->isStrictFPOpcode() ? ISD::STRICT_FSUB : ISD::FSUB, SrcVT))
7820  return false;
7821 
7822  SDValue Cst = DAG.getConstantFP(APF, dl, SrcVT);
7823  SDValue Sel;
7824 
7825  if (Node->isStrictFPOpcode()) {
7826  Sel = DAG.getSetCC(dl, SetCCVT, Src, Cst, ISD::SETLT,
7827  Node->getOperand(0), /*IsSignaling*/ true);
7828  Chain = Sel.getValue(1);
7829  } else {
7830  Sel = DAG.getSetCC(dl, SetCCVT, Src, Cst, ISD::SETLT);
7831  }
7832 
7833  bool Strict = Node->isStrictFPOpcode() ||
7834  shouldUseStrictFP_TO_INT(SrcVT, DstVT, /*IsSigned*/ false);
7835 
7836  if (Strict) {
7837  // Expand based on maximum range of FP_TO_SINT, if the value exceeds the
7838  // signmask then offset (the result of which should be fully representable).
7839  // Sel = Src < 0x8000000000000000
7840  // FltOfs = select Sel, 0, 0x8000000000000000
7841  // IntOfs = select Sel, 0, 0x8000000000000000
7842  // Result = fp_to_sint(Src - FltOfs) ^ IntOfs
7843 
7844  // TODO: Should any fast-math-flags be set for the FSUB?
7845  SDValue FltOfs = DAG.getSelect(dl, SrcVT, Sel,
7846  DAG.getConstantFP(0.0, dl, SrcVT), Cst);
7847  Sel = DAG.getBoolExtOrTrunc(Sel, dl, DstSetCCVT, DstVT);
7848  SDValue IntOfs = DAG.getSelect(dl, DstVT, Sel,
7849  DAG.getConstant(0, dl, DstVT),
7850  DAG.getConstant(SignMask, dl, DstVT));
7851  SDValue SInt;
7852  if (Node->isStrictFPOpcode()) {
7853  SDValue Val = DAG.getNode(ISD::STRICT_FSUB, dl, { SrcVT, MVT::Other },
7854  { Chain, Src, FltOfs });
7855  SInt = DAG.getNode(ISD::STRICT_FP_TO_SINT, dl, { DstVT, MVT::Other },
7856  { Val.getValue(1), Val });
7857  Chain = SInt.getValue(1);
7858  } else {
7859  SDValue Val = DAG.getNode(ISD::FSUB, dl, SrcVT, Src, FltOfs);
7860  SInt = DAG.getNode(ISD::FP_TO_SINT, dl, DstVT, Val);
7861  }
7862  Result = DAG.getNode(ISD::XOR, dl, DstVT, SInt, IntOfs);
7863  } else {
7864  // Expand based on maximum range of FP_TO_SINT:
7865  // True = fp_to_sint(Src)
7866  // False = 0x8000000000000000 + fp_to_sint(Src - 0x8000000000000000)
7867  // Result = select (Src < 0x8000000000000000), True, False
7868 
7869  SDValue True = DAG.getNode(ISD::FP_TO_SINT, dl, DstVT, Src);
7870  // TODO: Should any fast-math-flags be set for the FSUB?
7871  SDValue False = DAG.getNode(ISD::FP_TO_SINT, dl, DstVT,
7872  DAG.getNode(ISD::FSUB, dl, SrcVT, Src, Cst));
7873  False = DAG.getNode(ISD::XOR, dl, DstVT, False,
7874  DAG.getConstant(SignMask, dl, DstVT));
7875  Sel = DAG.getBoolExtOrTrunc(Sel, dl, DstSetCCVT, DstVT);
7876  Result = DAG.getSelect(dl, DstVT, Sel, True, False);
7877  }
7878  return true;
7879 }
7880 
7881 bool TargetLowering::expandUINT_TO_FP(SDNode *Node, SDValue &Result,
7882  SDValue &Chain,
7883  SelectionDAG &DAG) const {
7884  // This transform is not correct for converting 0 when rounding mode is set
7885  // to round toward negative infinity which will produce -0.0. So disable under
7886  // strictfp.
7887  if (Node->isStrictFPOpcode())
7888  return false;
7889 
7890  SDValue Src = Node->getOperand(0);
7891  EVT SrcVT = Src.getValueType();
7892  EVT DstVT = Node->getValueType(0);
7893 
7894  if (SrcVT.getScalarType() != MVT::i64 || DstVT.getScalarType() != MVT::f64)
7895  return false;
7896 
7897  // Only expand vector types if we have the appropriate vector bit operations.
7898  if (SrcVT.isVector() && (!isOperationLegalOrCustom(ISD::SRL, SrcVT) ||
7899  !isOperationLegalOrCustom(ISD::FADD, DstVT) ||
7900  !isOperationLegalOrCustom(ISD::FSUB, DstVT) ||
7901  !isOperationLegalOrCustomOrPromote(ISD::OR, SrcVT) ||
7902  !isOperationLegalOrCustomOrPromote(ISD::AND, SrcVT)))
7903  return false;
7904 
7905  SDLoc dl(SDValue(Node, 0));
7906  EVT ShiftVT = getShiftAmountTy(SrcVT, DAG.getDataLayout());
7907 
7908  // Implementation of unsigned i64 to f64 following the algorithm in
7909  // __floatundidf in compiler_rt. This implementation performs rounding
7910  // correctly in all rounding modes with the exception of converting 0
7911  // when rounding toward negative infinity. In that case the fsub will produce
7912  // -0.0. This will be added to +0.0 and produce -0.0 which is incorrect.
7913  SDValue TwoP52 = DAG.getConstant(UINT64_C(0x4330000000000000), dl, SrcVT);
7914  SDValue TwoP84PlusTwoP52 = DAG.getConstantFP(
7915  llvm::bit_cast<double>(UINT64_C(0x4530000000100000)), dl, DstVT);
7916  SDValue TwoP84 = DAG.getConstant(UINT64_C(0x4530000000000000), dl, SrcVT);
7917  SDValue LoMask = DAG.getConstant(UINT64_C(0x00000000FFFFFFFF), dl, SrcVT);
7918  SDValue HiShift = DAG.getConstant(32, dl, ShiftVT);
7919 
7920  SDValue Lo = DAG.getNode(ISD::AND, dl, SrcVT, Src, LoMask);
7921  SDValue Hi = DAG.getNode(ISD::SRL, dl, SrcVT, Src, HiShift);
7922  SDValue LoOr = DAG.getNode(ISD::OR, dl, SrcVT, Lo, TwoP52);
7923  SDValue HiOr = DAG.getNode(ISD::OR, dl, SrcVT, Hi, TwoP84);
7924  SDValue LoFlt = DAG.getBitcast(DstVT, LoOr);
7925  SDValue HiFlt = DAG.getBitcast(DstVT, HiOr);
7926  SDValue HiSub =
7927  DAG.getNode(ISD::FSUB, dl, DstVT, HiFlt, TwoP84PlusTwoP52);
7928  Result = DAG.getNode(ISD::FADD, dl, DstVT, LoFlt, HiSub);
7929  return true;
7930 }
7931 
7932 SDValue
7933 TargetLowering::createSelectForFMINNUM_FMAXNUM(SDNode *Node,
7934  SelectionDAG &DAG) const {
7935  unsigned Opcode = Node->getOpcode();
7936  assert((Opcode == ISD::FMINNUM || Opcode == ISD::FMAXNUM ||
7937  Opcode == ISD::STRICT_FMINNUM || Opcode == ISD::STRICT_FMAXNUM) &&
7938  "Wrong opcode");
7939 
7940  if (Node->getFlags().hasNoNaNs()) {
7941  ISD::CondCode Pred = Opcode == ISD::FMINNUM ? ISD::SETLT : ISD::SETGT;
7942  SDValue Op1 = Node->getOperand(0);
7943  SDValue Op2 = Node->getOperand(1);
7944  SDValue SelCC = DAG.getSelectCC(SDLoc(Node), Op1, Op2, Op1, Op2, Pred);
7945  // Copy FMF flags, but always set the no-signed-zeros flag
7946  // as this is implied by the FMINNUM/FMAXNUM semantics.
7947  SDNodeFlags Flags = Node->getFlags();
7948  Flags.setNoSignedZeros(true);
7949  SelCC->setFlags(Flags);
7950  return SelCC;
7951  }
7952 
7953  return SDValue();
7954 }
7955 
7956 SDValue TargetLowering::expandFMINNUM_FMAXNUM(SDNode *Node,
7957  SelectionDAG &DAG) const {
7958  SDLoc dl(Node);
7959  unsigned NewOp = Node->getOpcode() == ISD::FMINNUM ?
7960  ISD::FMINNUM_IEEE : ISD::FMAXNUM_IEEE;
7961  EVT VT = Node->getValueType(0);
7962 
7963  if (VT.isScalableVector())
7964  report_fatal_error(
7965  "Expanding fminnum/fmaxnum for scalable vectors is undefined.");
7966 
7967  if (isOperationLegalOrCustom(NewOp, VT)) {
7968  SDValue Quiet0 = Node->getOperand(0);
7969  SDValue Quiet1 = Node->getOperand(1);
7970 
7971  if (!Node->getFlags().hasNoNaNs()) {
7972  // Insert canonicalizes if it's possible we need to quiet to get correct
7973  // sNaN behavior.
7974  if (!DAG.isKnownNeverSNaN(Quiet0)) {
7975  Quiet0 = DAG.getNode(ISD::FCANONICALIZE, dl, VT, Quiet0,
7976  Node->getFlags());
7977  }
7978  if (!DAG.isKnownNeverSNaN(Quiet1)) {
7979  Quiet1 = DAG.getNode(ISD::FCANONICALIZE, dl, VT, Quiet1,
7980  Node->getFlags());
7981  }
7982  }
7983 
7984  return DAG.getNode(NewOp, dl, VT, Quiet0, Quiet1, Node->getFlags());
7985  }
7986 
7987  // If the target has FMINIMUM/FMAXIMUM but not FMINNUM/FMAXNUM use that
7988  // instead if there are no NaNs and there can't be an incompatiable zero
7989  // compare: at least one operand isn't +/-0, or there are no signed-zeros.
7990  if (Node->getFlags().hasNoNaNs() &&
7991  (Node->getFlags().hasNoSignedZeros() ||
7992  DAG.isKnownNeverZeroFloat(Node->getOperand(0)) ||
7993  DAG.isKnownNeverZeroFloat(Node->getOperand(1)))) {
7994  unsigned IEEE2018Op =
7995  Node->getOpcode() == ISD::FMINNUM ? ISD::FMINIMUM : ISD::FMAXIMUM;
7996  if (isOperationLegalOrCustom(IEEE2018Op, VT))
7997  return DAG.getNode(IEEE2018Op, dl, VT, Node->getOperand(0),
7998  Node->getOperand(1), Node->getFlags());
7999  }
8000 
8001  if (SDValue SelCC = createSelectForFMINNUM_FMAXNUM(Node, DAG))
8002  return SelCC;
8003 
8004  return SDValue();
8005 }
8006 
8007 SDValue TargetLowering::expandIS_FPCLASS(EVT ResultVT, SDValue Op,
8008  unsigned Test, SDNodeFlags Flags,
8009  const SDLoc &DL,
8010  SelectionDAG &DAG) const {
8011  EVT OperandVT = Op.getValueType();
8012  assert(OperandVT.isFloatingPoint());
8013 
8014  // Degenerated cases.
8015  if (Test == 0)
8016  return DAG.getBoolConstant(false, DL, ResultVT, OperandVT);
8017  if ((Test & fcAllFlags) == fcAllFlags)
8018  return DAG.getBoolConstant(true, DL, ResultVT, OperandVT);
8019 
8020  // PPC double double is a pair of doubles, of which the higher part determines
8021  // the value class.
8022  if (OperandVT == MVT::ppcf128) {
8023  Op = DAG.getNode(ISD::EXTRACT_ELEMENT, DL, MVT::f64, Op,
8024  DAG.getConstant(1, DL, MVT::i32));
8025  OperandVT = MVT::f64;
8026  }
8027 
8028  // Some checks may be represented as inversion of simpler check, for example
8029  // "inf|normal|subnormal|zero" => !"nan".
8030  bool IsInverted = false;
8031  if (unsigned InvertedCheck = getInvertedFPClassTest(Test)) {
8032  IsInverted = true;
8033  Test = InvertedCheck;
8034  }
8035 
8036  // Floating-point type properties.
8037  EVT ScalarFloatVT = OperandVT.getScalarType();
8038  const Type *FloatTy = ScalarFloatVT.getTypeForEVT(*DAG.getContext());
8039  const llvm::fltSemantics &Semantics = FloatTy->getFltSemantics();
8040  bool IsF80 = (ScalarFloatVT == MVT::f80);
8041 
8042  // Some checks can be implemented using float comparisons, if floating point
8043  // exceptions are ignored.
8044  if (Flags.hasNoFPExcept() &&
8045  isOperationLegalOrCustom(ISD::SETCC, OperandVT.getScalarType())) {
8046  if (Test == fcZero) {
8047  DenormalMode Mode = DAG.getMachineFunction().getDenormalMode(Semantics);
8048  if (Mode.Input == DenormalMode::IEEE) {
8049  // If denormals could be implicitly treated as 0, this is not equivalent
8050  // to a compare with 0 since it will also be true for denormals.
8051  //
8052  // TODO: With DAZ, check == fcZero | fcSubnormal
8053  return DAG.getSetCC(DL, ResultVT, Op,
8054  DAG.getConstantFP(0.0, DL, OperandVT),
8055  IsInverted ? ISD::SETUNE : ISD::SETOEQ);
8056  }
8057  }
8058 
8059  if (Test == fcNan)
8060  return DAG.getSetCC(DL, ResultVT, Op, Op,
8061  IsInverted ? ISD::SETO : ISD::SETUO);
8062  }
8063 
8064  // In the general case use integer operations.
8065  unsigned BitSize = OperandVT.getScalarSizeInBits();
8066  EVT IntVT = EVT::getIntegerVT(*DAG.getContext(), BitSize);
8067  if (OperandVT.isVector())
8068  IntVT = EVT::getVectorVT(*DAG.getContext(), IntVT,
8069  OperandVT.getVectorElementCount());
8070  SDValue OpAsInt = DAG.getBitcast(IntVT, Op);
8071 
8072  // Various masks.
8073  APInt SignBit = APInt::getSignMask(BitSize);
8074  APInt ValueMask = APInt::getSignedMaxValue(BitSize); // All bits but sign.
8075  APInt Inf = APFloat::getInf(Semantics).bitcastToAPInt(); // Exp and int bit.
8076  const unsigned ExplicitIntBitInF80 = 63;
8077  APInt ExpMask = Inf;
8078  if (IsF80)
8079  ExpMask.clearBit(ExplicitIntBitInF80);
8080  APInt AllOneMantissa = APFloat::getLargest(Semantics).bitcastToAPInt() & ~Inf;
8081  APInt QNaNBitMask =
8082  APInt::getOneBitSet(BitSize, AllOneMantissa.getActiveBits() - 1);
8083  APInt InvertionMask = APInt::getAllOnesValue(ResultVT.getScalarSizeInBits());
8084 
8085  SDValue ValueMaskV = DAG.getConstant(ValueMask, DL, IntVT);
8086  SDValue SignBitV = DAG.getConstant(SignBit, DL, IntVT);
8087  SDValue ExpMaskV = DAG.getConstant(ExpMask, DL, IntVT);
8088  SDValue ZeroV = DAG.getConstant(0, DL, IntVT);
8089  SDValue InfV = DAG.getConstant(Inf, DL, IntVT);
8090  SDValue ResultInvertionMask = DAG.getConstant(InvertionMask, DL, ResultVT);
8091 
8092  SDValue Res;
8093  const auto appendResult = [&](SDValue PartialRes) {
8094  if (PartialRes) {
8095  if (Res)
8096  Res = DAG.getNode(ISD::OR, DL, ResultVT, Res, PartialRes);
8097  else
8098  Res = PartialRes;
8099  }
8100  };
8101 
8102  SDValue IntBitIsSetV; // Explicit integer bit in f80 mantissa is set.
8103  const auto getIntBitIsSet = [&]() -> SDValue {
8104  if (!IntBitIsSetV) {
8105  APInt IntBitMask(BitSize, 0);
8106  IntBitMask.setBit(ExplicitIntBitInF80);
8107  SDValue IntBitMaskV = DAG.getConstant(IntBitMask, DL, IntVT);
8108  SDValue IntBitV = DAG.getNode(ISD::AND, DL, IntVT, OpAsInt, IntBitMaskV);
8109  IntBitIsSetV = DAG.getSetCC(DL, ResultVT, IntBitV, ZeroV, ISD::SETNE);
8110  }
8111  return IntBitIsSetV;
8112  };
8113 
8114  // Split the value into sign bit and absolute value.
8115  SDValue AbsV = DAG.getNode(ISD::AND, DL, IntVT, OpAsInt, ValueMaskV);
8116  SDValue SignV = DAG.getSetCC(DL, ResultVT, OpAsInt,
8117  DAG.getConstant(0.0, DL, IntVT), ISD::SETLT);
8118 
8119  // Tests that involve more than one class should be processed first.
8120  SDValue PartialRes;
8121 
8122  if (IsF80)
8123  ; // Detect finite numbers of f80 by checking individual classes because
8124  // they have different settings of the explicit integer bit.
8125  else if ((Test & fcFinite) == fcFinite) {
8126  // finite(V) ==> abs(V) < exp_mask
8127  PartialRes = DAG.getSetCC(DL, ResultVT, AbsV, ExpMaskV, ISD::SETLT);
8128  Test &= ~fcFinite;
8129  } else if ((Test & fcFinite) == fcPosFinite) {
8130  // finite(V) && V > 0 ==> V < exp_mask
8131  PartialRes = DAG.getSetCC(DL, ResultVT, OpAsInt, ExpMaskV, ISD::SETULT);
8132  Test &= ~fcPosFinite;
8133  } else if ((Test & fcFinite) == fcNegFinite) {
8134  // finite(V) && V < 0 ==> abs(V) < exp_mask && signbit == 1
8135  PartialRes = DAG.getSetCC(DL, ResultVT, AbsV, ExpMaskV, ISD::SETLT);
8136  PartialRes = DAG.getNode(ISD::AND, DL, ResultVT, PartialRes, SignV);
8137  Test &= ~fcNegFinite;
8138  }
8139  appendResult(PartialRes);
8140 
8141  // Check for individual classes.
8142 
8143  if (unsigned PartialCheck = Test & fcZero) {
8144  if (PartialCheck == fcPosZero)
8145  PartialRes = DAG.getSetCC(DL, ResultVT, OpAsInt, ZeroV, ISD::SETEQ);
8146  else if (PartialCheck == fcZero)
8147  PartialRes = DAG.getSetCC(DL, ResultVT, AbsV, ZeroV, ISD::SETEQ);
8148  else // ISD::fcNegZero
8149  PartialRes = DAG.getSetCC(DL, ResultVT, OpAsInt, SignBitV, ISD::SETEQ);
8150  appendResult(PartialRes);
8151  }
8152 
8153  if (unsigned PartialCheck = Test & fcInf) {
8154  if (PartialCheck == fcPosInf)
8155  PartialRes = DAG.getSetCC(DL, ResultVT, OpAsInt, InfV, ISD::SETEQ);
8156  else if (PartialCheck == fcInf)
8157  PartialRes = DAG.getSetCC(DL, ResultVT, AbsV, InfV, ISD::SETEQ);
8158  else { // ISD::fcNegInf
8159  APInt NegInf = APFloat::getInf(Semantics, true).bitcastToAPInt();
8160  SDValue NegInfV = DAG.getConstant(NegInf, DL, IntVT);
8161  PartialRes = DAG.getSetCC(DL, ResultVT, OpAsInt, NegInfV, ISD::SETEQ);
8162  }
8163  appendResult(PartialRes);
8164  }
8165 
8166  if (unsigned PartialCheck = Test & fcNan) {
8167  APInt InfWithQnanBit = Inf | QNaNBitMask;
8168  SDValue InfWithQnanBitV = DAG.getConstant(InfWithQnanBit, DL, IntVT);
8169  if (PartialCheck == fcNan) {
8170  // isnan(V) ==> abs(V) > int(inf)
8171  PartialRes = DAG.getSetCC(DL, ResultVT, AbsV, InfV, ISD::SETGT);
8172  if (IsF80) {
8173  // Recognize unsupported values as NaNs for compatibility with glibc.
8174  // In them (exp(V)==0) == int_bit.
8175  SDValue ExpBits = DAG.getNode(ISD::AND, DL, IntVT, AbsV, ExpMaskV);
8176  SDValue ExpIsZero =
8177  DAG.getSetCC(DL, ResultVT, ExpBits, ZeroV, ISD::SETEQ);
8178  SDValue IsPseudo =
8179  DAG.getSetCC(DL, ResultVT, getIntBitIsSet(), ExpIsZero, ISD::SETEQ);
8180  PartialRes = DAG.getNode(ISD::OR, DL, ResultVT, PartialRes, IsPseudo);
8181  }
8182  } else if (PartialCheck == fcQNan) {
8183  // isquiet(V) ==> abs(V) >= (unsigned(Inf) | quiet_bit)
8184  PartialRes =
8185  DAG.getSetCC(DL, ResultVT, AbsV, InfWithQnanBitV, ISD::SETGE);
8186  } else { // ISD::fcSNan
8187  // issignaling(V) ==> abs(V) > unsigned(Inf) &&
8188  // abs(V) < (unsigned(Inf) | quiet_bit)
8189  SDValue IsNan = DAG.getSetCC(DL, ResultVT, AbsV, InfV, ISD::SETGT);
8190  SDValue IsNotQnan =
8191  DAG.getSetCC(DL, ResultVT, AbsV, InfWithQnanBitV, ISD::SETLT);
8192  PartialRes = DAG.getNode(ISD::AND, DL, ResultVT, IsNan, IsNotQnan);
8193  }
8194  appendResult(PartialRes);
8195  }
8196 
8197  if (unsigned PartialCheck = Test & fcSubnormal) {
8198  // issubnormal(V) ==> unsigned(abs(V) - 1) < (all mantissa bits set)
8199  // issubnormal(V) && V>0 ==> unsigned(V - 1) < (all mantissa bits set)
8200  SDValue V = (PartialCheck == fcPosSubnormal) ? OpAsInt : AbsV;
8201  SDValue MantissaV = DAG.getConstant(AllOneMantissa, DL, IntVT);
8202  SDValue VMinusOneV =
8203  DAG.getNode(ISD::SUB, DL, IntVT, V, DAG.getConstant(1, DL, IntVT));
8204  PartialRes = DAG.getSetCC(DL, ResultVT, VMinusOneV, MantissaV, ISD::SETULT);
8205  if (PartialCheck == fcNegSubnormal)
8206  PartialRes = DAG.getNode(ISD::AND, DL, ResultVT, PartialRes, SignV);
8207  appendResult(PartialRes);
8208  }
8209 
8210  if (unsigned PartialCheck = Test & fcNormal) {
8211  // isnormal(V) ==> (0 < exp < max_exp) ==> (unsigned(exp-1) < (max_exp-1))
8212  APInt ExpLSB = ExpMask & ~(ExpMask.shl(1));
8213  SDValue ExpLSBV = DAG.getConstant(ExpLSB, DL, IntVT);
8214  SDValue ExpMinus1 = DAG.getNode(ISD::SUB, DL, IntVT, AbsV, ExpLSBV);
8215  APInt ExpLimit = ExpMask - ExpLSB;
8216  SDValue ExpLimitV = DAG.getConstant(ExpLimit, DL, IntVT);
8217  PartialRes = DAG.getSetCC(DL, ResultVT, ExpMinus1, ExpLimitV, ISD::SETULT);
8218  if (PartialCheck == fcNegNormal)
8219  PartialRes = DAG.getNode(ISD::AND, DL, ResultVT, PartialRes, SignV);
8220  else if (PartialCheck == fcPosNormal) {
8221  SDValue PosSignV =
8222  DAG.getNode(ISD::XOR, DL, ResultVT, SignV, ResultInvertionMask);
8223  PartialRes = DAG.getNode(ISD::AND, DL, ResultVT, PartialRes, PosSignV);
8224  }
8225  if (IsF80)
8226  PartialRes =
8227  DAG.getNode(ISD::AND, DL, ResultVT, PartialRes, getIntBitIsSet());
8228  appendResult(PartialRes);
8229  }
8230 
8231  if (!Res)
8232  return DAG.getConstant(IsInverted, DL, ResultVT);
8233  if (IsInverted)
8234  Res = DAG.getNode(ISD::XOR, DL, ResultVT, Res, ResultInvertionMask);
8235  return Res;
8236 }
8237 
8238 // Only expand vector types if we have the appropriate vector bit operations.
8239 static bool canExpandVectorCTPOP(const TargetLowering &TLI, EVT VT) {
8240  assert(VT.isVector() && "Expected vector type");
8241  unsigned Len = VT.getScalarSizeInBits();
8242  return TLI.isOperationLegalOrCustom(ISD::ADD, VT) &&
8243  TLI.isOperationLegalOrCustom(ISD::SUB, VT) &&
8244  TLI.isOperationLegalOrCustom(ISD::SRL, VT) &&
8245  (Len == 8 || TLI.isOperationLegalOrCustom(ISD::MUL, VT)) &&
8246  TLI.isOperationLegalOrCustomOrPromote(ISD::AND, VT);
8247 }
8248 
8249 SDValue TargetLowering::expandCTPOP(SDNode *Node, SelectionDAG &DAG) const {
8250  SDLoc dl(Node);
8251  EVT VT = Node->getValueType(0);
8252  EVT ShVT = getShiftAmountTy(VT, DAG.getDataLayout());
8253  SDValue Op = Node->getOperand(0);
8254  unsigned Len = VT.getScalarSizeInBits();
8255  assert(VT.isInteger() && "CTPOP not implemented for this type.");
8256 
8257  // TODO: Add support for irregular type lengths.
8258  if (!(Len <= 128 && Len % 8 == 0))
8259  return SDValue();
8260 
8261  // Only expand vector types if we have the appropriate vector bit operations.
8262  if (VT.isVector() && !canExpandVectorCTPOP(*this, VT))
8263  return SDValue();
8264 
8265  // This is the "best" algorithm from
8266  // http://graphics.stanford.edu/~seander/bithacks.html#CountBitsSetParallel
8267  SDValue Mask55 =
8268  DAG.getConstant(APInt::getSplat(Len, APInt(8, 0x55)), dl, VT);
8269  SDValue Mask33 =
8270  DAG.getConstant(APInt::getSplat(Len, APInt(8, 0x33)), dl, VT);
8271  SDValue Mask0F =
8272  DAG.getConstant(APInt::getSplat(Len, APInt(8, 0x0F)), dl, VT);
8273 
8274  // v = v - ((v >> 1) & 0x55555555...)
8275  Op = DAG.getNode(ISD::SUB, dl, VT, Op,
8276  DAG.getNode(ISD::AND, dl, VT,
8277  DAG.getNode(ISD::SRL, dl, VT, Op,
8278  DAG.getConstant(1, dl, ShVT)),
8279  Mask55));
8280  // v = (v & 0x33333333...) + ((v >> 2) & 0x33333333...)
8281  Op = DAG.getNode(ISD::ADD, dl, VT, DAG.getNode(ISD::AND, dl, VT, Op, Mask33),
8282  DAG.getNode(ISD::AND, dl, VT,
8283  DAG.getNode(ISD::SRL, dl, VT, Op,
8284  DAG.getConstant(2, dl, ShVT)),
8285  Mask33));
8286  // v = (v + (v >> 4)) & 0x0F0F0F0F...
8287  Op = DAG.getNode(ISD::AND, dl, VT,
8288  DAG.getNode(ISD::ADD, dl, VT, Op,
8289  DAG.getNode(ISD::SRL, dl, VT, Op,
8290  DAG.getConstant(4, dl, ShVT))),
8291  Mask0F);
8292 
8293  if (Len <= 8)
8294  return Op;
8295 
8296  // Avoid the multiply if we only have 2 bytes to add.
8297  // TODO: Only doing this for scalars because vectors weren't as obviously
8298  // improved.
8299  if (Len == 16 && !VT.isVector()) {
8300  // v = (v + (v >> 8)) & 0x00FF;
8301  return DAG.getNode(ISD::AND, dl, VT,
8302  DAG.getNode(ISD::ADD, dl, VT, Op,
8303  DAG.getNode(ISD::SRL, dl, VT, Op,
8304  DAG.getConstant(8, dl, ShVT))),
8305  DAG.getConstant(0xFF, dl, VT));
8306  }
8307 
8308  // v = (v * 0x01010101...) >> (Len - 8)
8309  SDValue Mask01 =
8310  DAG.getConstant(APInt::getSplat(Len, APInt(8, 0x01)), dl, VT);
8311  return DAG.getNode(ISD::SRL, dl, VT,
8312  DAG.getNode(ISD::MUL, dl, VT, Op, Mask01),
8313  DAG.getConstant(Len - 8, dl, ShVT));
8314 }
8315 
8316 SDValue TargetLowering::expandVPCTPOP(SDNode *Node, SelectionDAG &DAG) const {
8317  SDLoc dl(Node);
8318  EVT VT = Node->getValueType(0);
8319  EVT ShVT = getShiftAmountTy(VT, DAG.getDataLayout());
8320  SDValue Op = Node->getOperand(0);
8321  SDValue Mask = Node->getOperand(1);
8322  SDValue VL = Node->getOperand(2);
8323  unsigned Len = VT.getScalarSizeInBits();
8324  assert(VT.isInteger() && "VP_CTPOP not implemented for this type.");
8325 
8326  // TODO: Add support for irregular type lengths.
8327  if (!(Len <= 128 && Len % 8 == 0))
8328  return SDValue();
8329 
8330  // This is same algorithm of expandCTPOP from
8331  // http://graphics.stanford.edu/~seander/bithacks.html#CountBitsSetParallel
8332  SDValue Mask55 =
8333  DAG.getConstant(APInt::getSplat(Len, APInt(8, 0x55)), dl, VT);
8334  SDValue Mask33 =
8335  DAG.getConstant(APInt::getSplat(Len, APInt(8, 0x33)), dl, VT);
8336  SDValue Mask0F =
8337  DAG.getConstant(APInt::getSplat(Len, APInt(8, 0x0F)), dl, VT);
8338 
8339  SDValue Tmp1, Tmp2, Tmp3, Tmp4, Tmp5;
8340 
8341  // v = v - ((v >> 1) & 0x55555555...)
8342  Tmp1 = DAG.getNode(ISD::VP_AND, dl, VT,
8343  DAG.getNode(ISD::VP_LSHR, dl, VT, Op,
8344  DAG.getConstant(1, dl, ShVT), Mask, VL),
8345  Mask55, Mask, VL);
8346  Op = DAG.getNode(ISD::VP_SUB, dl, VT, Op, Tmp1, Mask, VL);
8347 
8348  // v = (v & 0x33333333...) + ((v >> 2) & 0x33333333...)
8349  Tmp2 = DAG.getNode(ISD::VP_AND, dl, VT, Op, Mask33, Mask, VL);
8350  Tmp3 = DAG.getNode(ISD::VP_AND, dl, VT,
8351  DAG.getNode(ISD::VP_LSHR, dl, VT, Op,
8352  DAG.getConstant(2, dl, ShVT), Mask, VL),
8353  Mask33, Mask, VL);
8354  Op = DAG.getNode(ISD::VP_ADD, dl, VT, Tmp2, Tmp3, Mask, VL);
8355 
8356  // v = (v + (v >> 4)) & 0x0F0F0F0F...
8357  Tmp4 = DAG.getNode(ISD::VP_LSHR, dl, VT, Op, DAG.getConstant(4, dl, ShVT),
8358  Mask, VL),
8359  Tmp5 = DAG.getNode(ISD::VP_ADD, dl, VT, Op, Tmp4, Mask, VL);
8360  Op = DAG.getNode(ISD::VP_AND, dl, VT, Tmp5, Mask0F, Mask, VL);
8361 
8362  if (Len <= 8)
8363  return Op;
8364 
8365  // v = (v * 0x01010101...) >> (Len - 8)
8366  SDValue Mask01 =
8367  DAG.getConstant(APInt::getSplat(Len, APInt(8, 0x01)), dl, VT);
8368  return DAG.getNode(ISD::VP_LSHR, dl, VT,
8369  DAG.getNode(ISD::VP_MUL, dl, VT, Op, Mask01, Mask, VL),
8370  DAG.getConstant(Len - 8, dl, ShVT), Mask, VL);
8371 }
8372 
8373 SDValue TargetLowering::expandCTLZ(SDNode *Node, SelectionDAG &DAG) const {
8374  SDLoc dl(Node);
8375  EVT VT = Node->getValueType(0);
8376  EVT ShVT = getShiftAmountTy(VT, DAG.getDataLayout());
8377  SDValue Op = Node->getOperand(0);
8378  unsigned NumBitsPerElt = VT.getScalarSizeInBits();
8379 
8380  // If the non-ZERO_UNDEF version is supported we can use that instead.
8381  if (Node->getOpcode() == ISD::CTLZ_ZERO_UNDEF &&
8382  isOperationLegalOrCustom(ISD::CTLZ, VT))
8383  return DAG.getNode(ISD::CTLZ, dl, VT, Op);
8384 
8385  // If the ZERO_UNDEF version is supported use that and handle the zero case.
8386  if (isOperationLegalOrCustom(ISD::CTLZ_ZERO_UNDEF, VT)) {
8387  EVT SetCCVT =
8388  getSetCCResultType(DAG.getDataLayout(), *DAG.getContext(), VT);
8389  SDValue CTLZ = DAG.getNode(ISD::CTLZ_ZERO_UNDEF, dl, VT, Op);
8390  SDValue Zero = DAG.getConstant(0, dl, VT);
8391  SDValue SrcIsZero = DAG.getSetCC(dl, SetCCVT, Op, Zero, ISD::SETEQ);
8392  return DAG.getSelect(dl, VT, SrcIsZero,
8393  DAG.getConstant(NumBitsPerElt, dl, VT), CTLZ);
8394  }
8395 
8396  // Only expand vector types if we have the appropriate vector bit operations.
8397  // This includes the operations needed to expand CTPOP if it isn't supported.
8398  if (VT.isVector() && (!isPowerOf2_32(NumBitsPerElt) ||
8399  (!isOperationLegalOrCustom(ISD::CTPOP, VT) &&
8400  !canExpandVectorCTPOP(*this, VT)) ||
8401  !isOperationLegalOrCustom(ISD::SRL, VT) ||
8402  !isOperationLegalOrCustomOrPromote(ISD::OR, VT)))
8403  return SDValue();
8404 
8405  // for now, we do this:
8406  // x = x | (x >> 1);
8407  // x = x | (x >> 2);
8408  // ...
8409  // x = x | (x >>16);
8410  // x = x | (x >>32); // for 64-bit input
8411  // return popcount(~x);
8412  //
8413  // Ref: "Hacker's Delight" by Henry Warren
8414  for (unsigned i = 0; (1U << i) < NumBitsPerElt; ++i) {
8415  SDValue Tmp = DAG.getConstant(1ULL << i, dl, ShVT);
8416  Op = DAG.getNode(ISD::OR, dl, VT, Op,
8417  DAG.getNode(ISD::SRL, dl, VT, Op, Tmp));
8418  }
8419  Op = DAG.getNOT(dl, Op, VT);
8420  return DAG.getNode(ISD::CTPOP, dl, VT, Op);
8421 }
8422 
8423 SDValue TargetLowering::expandVPCTLZ(SDNode *Node, SelectionDAG &DAG) const {
8424  SDLoc dl(Node);
8425  EVT VT = Node->getValueType(0);
8426  EVT ShVT = getShiftAmountTy(VT, DAG.getDataLayout());
8427  SDValue Op = Node->getOperand(0);
8428  SDValue Mask = Node->getOperand(1);
8429  SDValue VL = Node->getOperand(2);
8430  unsigned NumBitsPerElt = VT.getScalarSizeInBits();
8431 
8432  // do this:
8433  // x = x | (x >> 1);
8434  // x = x | (x >> 2);
8435  // ...
8436  // x = x | (x >>16);
8437  // x = x | (x >>32); // for 64-bit input
8438  // return popcount(~x);
8439  for (unsigned i = 0; (1U << i) < NumBitsPerElt; ++i) {
8440  SDValue Tmp = DAG.getConstant(1ULL << i, dl, ShVT);
8441  Op = DAG.getNode(ISD::VP_OR, dl, VT, Op,
8442  DAG.getNode(ISD::VP_LSHR, dl, VT, Op, Tmp, Mask, VL), Mask,
8443  VL);
8444  }
8445  Op = DAG.getNode(ISD::VP_XOR, dl, VT, Op, DAG.getConstant(-1, dl, VT), Mask,
8446  VL);
8447  return DAG.getNode(ISD::VP_CTPOP, dl, VT, Op, Mask, VL);
8448 }
8449 
8450 SDValue TargetLowering::CTTZTableLookup(SDNode *Node, SelectionDAG &DAG,
8451  const SDLoc &DL, EVT VT, SDValue Op,
8452  unsigned BitWidth) const {
8453  if (BitWidth != 32 && BitWidth != 64)
8454  return SDValue();
8455  APInt DeBruijn = BitWidth == 32 ? APInt(32, 0x077CB531U)
8456  : APInt(64, 0x0218A392CD3D5DBFULL);
8457  const DataLayout &TD = DAG.getDataLayout();
8458  MachinePointerInfo PtrInfo =
8459  MachinePointerInfo::getConstantPool(DAG.getMachineFunction());
8460  unsigned ShiftAmt = BitWidth - Log2_32(BitWidth);
8461  SDValue Neg = DAG.getNode(ISD::SUB, DL, VT, DAG.getConstant(0, DL, VT), Op);
8462  SDValue Lookup = DAG.getNode(
8463  ISD::SRL, DL, VT,
8464  DAG.getNode(ISD::MUL, DL, VT, DAG.getNode(ISD::AND, DL, VT, Op, Neg),
8465  DAG.getConstant(DeBruijn, DL, VT)),
8466  DAG.getConstant(ShiftAmt, DL, VT));
8467  Lookup = DAG.getSExtOrTrunc(Lookup, DL, getPointerTy(TD));
8468 
8469  SmallVector<uint8_t> Table(BitWidth, 0);
8470  for (unsigned i = 0; i < BitWidth; i++) {
8471  APInt Shl = DeBruijn.shl(i);
8472  APInt Lshr = Shl.lshr(ShiftAmt);
8473  Table[Lshr.getZExtValue()] = i;
8474  }
8475 
8476  // Create a ConstantArray in Constant Pool
8477  auto *CA = ConstantDataArray::get(*DAG.getContext(), Table);
8478  SDValue CPIdx = DAG.getConstantPool(CA, getPointerTy(TD),
8479  TD.getPrefTypeAlign(CA->getType()));
8480  SDValue ExtLoad = DAG.getExtLoad(ISD::ZEXTLOAD, DL, VT, DAG.getEntryNode(),
8481  DAG.getMemBasePlusOffset(CPIdx, Lookup, DL),
8482  PtrInfo, MVT::i8);
8483  if (Node->getOpcode() == ISD::CTTZ_ZERO_UNDEF)
8484  return ExtLoad;
8485 
8486  EVT SetCCVT =
8487  getSetCCResultType(DAG.getDataLayout(), *DAG.getContext(), VT);
8488  SDValue Zero = DAG.getConstant(0, DL, VT);
8489  SDValue SrcIsZero = DAG.getSetCC(DL, SetCCVT, Op, Zero, ISD::SETEQ);
8490  return DAG.getSelect(DL, VT, SrcIsZero,
8491  DAG.getConstant(BitWidth, DL, VT), ExtLoad);
8492 }
8493 
8494 SDValue TargetLowering::expandCTTZ(SDNode *Node, SelectionDAG &DAG) const {
8495  SDLoc dl(Node);
8496  EVT VT = Node->getValueType(0);
8497  SDValue Op = Node->getOperand(0);
8498  unsigned NumBitsPerElt = VT.getScalarSizeInBits();
8499 
8500  // If the non-ZERO_UNDEF version is supported we can use that instead.
8501  if (Node->getOpcode() == ISD::CTTZ_ZERO_UNDEF &&
8502  isOperationLegalOrCustom(ISD::CTTZ, VT))
8503  return DAG.getNode(ISD::CTTZ, dl, VT, Op);
8504 
8505  // If the ZERO_UNDEF version is supported use that and handle the zero case.
8506  if (isOperationLegalOrCustom(ISD::CTTZ_ZERO_UNDEF, VT)) {
8507  EVT SetCCVT =
8508  getSetCCResultType(DAG.getDataLayout(), *DAG.getContext(), VT);
8509  SDValue CTTZ = DAG.getNode(ISD::CTTZ_ZERO_UNDEF, dl, VT, Op);
8510  SDValue Zero = DAG.getConstant(0, dl, VT);
8511  SDValue SrcIsZero = DAG.getSetCC(dl, SetCCVT, Op, Zero, ISD::SETEQ);
8512  return DAG.getSelect(dl, VT, SrcIsZero,
8513  DAG.getConstant(NumBitsPerElt, dl, VT), CTTZ);
8514  }
8515 
8516  // Only expand vector types if we have the appropriate vector bit operations.
8517  // This includes the operations needed to expand CTPOP if it isn't supported.
8518  if (VT.isVector() && (!isPowerOf2_32(NumBitsPerElt) ||
8519  (!isOperationLegalOrCustom(ISD::CTPOP, VT) &&
8520  !isOperationLegalOrCustom(ISD::CTLZ, VT) &&
8521  !canExpandVectorCTPOP(*this, VT)) ||
8522  !isOperationLegalOrCustom(ISD::SUB, VT) ||
8523  !isOperationLegalOrCustomOrPromote(ISD::AND, VT) ||
8524  !isOperationLegalOrCustomOrPromote(ISD::XOR, VT)))
8525  return SDValue();
8526 
8527  // Emit Table Lookup if ISD::CTLZ and ISD::CTPOP are not legal.
8528  if (!VT.isVector() && isOperationExpand(ISD::CTPOP, VT) &&
8529  !isOperationLegal(ISD::CTLZ, VT))
8530  if (SDValue V = CTTZTableLookup(Node, DAG, dl, VT, Op, NumBitsPerElt))
8531  return V;
8532 
8533  // for now, we use: { return popcount(~x & (x - 1)); }
8534  // unless the target has ctlz but not ctpop, in which case we use:
8535  // { return 32 - nlz(~x & (x-1)); }
8536  // Ref: "Hacker's Delight" by Henry Warren
8537  SDValue Tmp = DAG.getNode(
8538  ISD::AND, dl, VT, DAG.getNOT(dl, Op, VT),
8539  DAG.getNode(ISD::SUB, dl, VT, Op, DAG.getConstant(1, dl, VT)));
8540 
8541  // If ISD::CTLZ is legal and CTPOP isn't, then do that instead.
8542  if (isOperationLegal(ISD::CTLZ, VT) && !isOperationLegal(ISD::CTPOP, VT)) {
8543  return DAG.getNode(ISD::SUB, dl, VT, DAG.getConstant(NumBitsPerElt, dl, VT),
8544  DAG.getNode(ISD::CTLZ, dl, VT, Tmp));
8545  }
8546 
8547  return DAG.getNode(ISD::CTPOP, dl, VT, Tmp);
8548 }
8549 
8550 SDValue TargetLowering::expandVPCTTZ(SDNode *Node, SelectionDAG &DAG) const {
8551  SDValue Op = Node->getOperand(0);
8552  SDValue Mask = Node->getOperand(1);
8553  SDValue VL = Node->getOperand(2);
8554  SDLoc dl(Node);
8555  EVT VT = Node->getValueType(0);
8556 
8557  // Same as the vector part of expandCTTZ, use: popcount(~x & (x - 1))
8558  SDValue Not = DAG.getNode(ISD::VP_XOR, dl, VT, Op,
8559  DAG.getConstant(-1, dl, VT), Mask, VL);
8560  SDValue MinusOne = DAG.getNode(ISD::VP_SUB, dl, VT, Op,
8561  DAG.getConstant(1, dl, VT), Mask, VL);
8562  SDValue Tmp = DAG.getNode(ISD::VP_AND, dl, VT, Not, MinusOne, Mask, VL);
8563  return DAG.getNode(ISD::VP_CTPOP, dl, VT, Tmp, Mask, VL);
8564 }
8565 
8566 SDValue TargetLowering::expandABS(SDNode *N, SelectionDAG &DAG,
8567  bool IsNegative) const {
8568  SDLoc dl(N);
8569  EVT VT = N->getValueType(0);
8570  EVT ShVT = getShiftAmountTy(VT, DAG.getDataLayout());
8571  SDValue Op = N->getOperand(0);
8572 
8573  // abs(x) -> smax(x,sub(0,x))
8574  if (!IsNegative && isOperationLegal(ISD::SUB, VT) &&
8575  isOperationLegal(ISD::SMAX, VT)) {
8576  SDValue Zero = DAG.getConstant(0, dl, VT);
8577  return DAG.getNode(ISD::SMAX, dl, VT, Op,
8578  DAG.getNode(ISD::SUB, dl, VT, Zero, Op));
8579  }
8580 
8581  // abs(x) -> umin(x,sub(0,x))
8582  if (!IsNegative && isOperationLegal(ISD::SUB, VT) &&
8583  isOperationLegal(ISD::UMIN, VT)) {
8584  SDValue Zero = DAG.getConstant(0, dl, VT);
8585  Op = DAG.getFreeze(Op);
8586  return DAG.getNode(ISD::UMIN, dl, VT, Op,
8587  DAG.getNode(ISD::SUB, dl, VT, Zero, Op));
8588  }
8589 
8590  // 0 - abs(x) -> smin(x, sub(0,x))
8591  if (IsNegative && isOperationLegal(ISD::SUB, VT) &&
8592  isOperationLegal(ISD::SMIN, VT)) {
8593  Op = DAG.getFreeze(Op);
8594  SDValue Zero = DAG.getConstant(0, dl, VT);
8595  return DAG.getNode(ISD::SMIN, dl, VT, Op,
8596  DAG.getNode(ISD::SUB, dl, VT, Zero, Op));
8597  }
8598 
8599  // Only expand vector types if we have the appropriate vector operations.
8600  if (VT.isVector() &&
8601  (!isOperationLegalOrCustom(ISD::SRA, VT) ||
8602  (!IsNegative && !isOperationLegalOrCustom(ISD::ADD, VT)) ||
8603  (IsNegative && !isOperationLegalOrCustom(ISD::SUB, VT)) ||
8604  !isOperationLegalOrCustomOrPromote(ISD::XOR, VT)))
8605  return SDValue();
8606 
8607  Op = DAG.getFreeze(Op);
8608  SDValue Shift =
8609  DAG.getNode(ISD::SRA, dl, VT, Op,
8610  DAG.getConstant(VT.getScalarSizeInBits() - 1, dl, ShVT));
8611  SDValue Xor = DAG.getNode(ISD::XOR, dl, VT, Op, Shift);
8612 
8613  // abs(x) -> Y = sra (X, size(X)-1); sub (xor (X, Y), Y)
8614  if (!IsNegative)
8615  return DAG.getNode(ISD::SUB, dl, VT, Xor, Shift);
8616 
8617  // 0 - abs(x) -> Y = sra (X, size(X)-1); sub (Y, xor (X, Y))
8618  return DAG.getNode(ISD::SUB, dl, VT, Shift, Xor);
8619 }
8620 
8621 SDValue TargetLowering::expandBSWAP(SDNode *N, SelectionDAG &DAG) const {
8622  SDLoc dl(N);
8623  EVT VT = N->getValueType(0);
8624  SDValue Op = N->getOperand(0);
8625 
8626  if (!VT.isSimple())
8627  return SDValue();
8628 
8629  EVT SHVT = getShiftAmountTy(VT, DAG.getDataLayout());
8630  SDValue Tmp1, Tmp2, Tmp3, Tmp4, Tmp5, Tmp6, Tmp7, Tmp8;
8631  switch (VT.getSimpleVT().getScalarType().SimpleTy) {
8632  default:
8633  return SDValue();
8634  case MVT::i16:
8635  // Use a rotate by 8. This can be further expanded if necessary.
8636  return DAG.getNode(ISD::ROTL, dl, VT, Op, DAG.getConstant(8, dl, SHVT));
8637  case MVT::i32:
8638  Tmp4 = DAG.getNode(ISD::SHL, dl, VT, Op, DAG.getConstant(24, dl, SHVT));
8639  Tmp3 = DAG.getNode(ISD::AND, dl, VT, Op,
8640  DAG.getConstant(0xFF00, dl, VT));
8641  Tmp3 = DAG.getNode(ISD::SHL, dl, VT, Tmp3, DAG.getConstant(8, dl, SHVT));
8642  Tmp2 = DAG.getNode(ISD::SRL, dl, VT, Op, DAG.getConstant(8, dl, SHVT));
8643  Tmp2 = DAG.getNode(ISD::AND, dl, VT, Tmp2, DAG.getConstant(0xFF00, dl, VT));
8644  Tmp1 = DAG.getNode(ISD::SRL, dl, VT, Op, DAG.getConstant(24, dl, SHVT));
8645  Tmp4 = DAG.getNode(ISD::OR, dl, VT, Tmp4, Tmp3);
8646  Tmp2 = DAG.getNode(ISD::OR, dl, VT, Tmp2, Tmp1);
8647  return DAG.getNode(ISD::OR, dl, VT, Tmp4, Tmp2);
8648  case MVT::i64:
8649  Tmp8 = DAG.getNode(ISD::SHL, dl, VT, Op, DAG.getConstant(56, dl, SHVT));
8650  Tmp7 = DAG.getNode(ISD::AND, dl, VT, Op,
8651  DAG.getConstant(255ULL<<8, dl, VT));
8652  Tmp7 = DAG.getNode(ISD::SHL, dl, VT, Tmp7, DAG.getConstant(40, dl, SHVT));
8653  Tmp6 = DAG.getNode(ISD::AND, dl, VT, Op,
8654  DAG.getConstant(255ULL<<16, dl, VT));
8655  Tmp6 = DAG.getNode(ISD::SHL, dl, VT, Tmp6, DAG.getConstant(24, dl, SHVT));
8656  Tmp5 = DAG.getNode(ISD::AND, dl, VT, Op,
8657  DAG.getConstant(255ULL<<24, dl, VT));
8658  Tmp5 = DAG.getNode(ISD::SHL, dl, VT, Tmp5, DAG.getConstant(8, dl, SHVT));
8659  Tmp4 = DAG.getNode(ISD::SRL, dl, VT, Op, DAG.getConstant(8, dl, SHVT));
8660  Tmp4 = DAG.getNode(ISD::AND, dl, VT, Tmp4,
8661  DAG.getConstant(255ULL<<24, dl, VT));
8662  Tmp3 = DAG.getNode(ISD::SRL, dl, VT, Op, DAG.getConstant(24, dl, SHVT));
8663  Tmp3 = DAG.getNode(ISD::AND, dl, VT, Tmp3,
8664  DAG.getConstant(255ULL<<16, dl, VT));
8665  Tmp2 = DAG.getNode(ISD::SRL, dl, VT, Op, DAG.getConstant(40, dl, SHVT));
8666  Tmp2 = DAG.getNode(ISD::AND, dl, VT, Tmp2,
8667  DAG.getConstant(255ULL<<8, dl, VT));
8668  Tmp1 = DAG.getNode(ISD::SRL, dl, VT, Op, DAG.getConstant(56, dl, SHVT));
8669  Tmp8 = DAG.getNode(ISD::OR, dl, VT, Tmp8, Tmp7);
8670  Tmp6 = DAG.getNode(ISD::OR, dl, VT, Tmp6, Tmp5);
8671  Tmp4 = DAG.getNode(ISD::OR, dl, VT, Tmp4, Tmp3);
8672  Tmp2 = DAG.getNode(ISD::OR, dl, VT, Tmp2, Tmp1);
8673  Tmp8 = DAG.getNode(ISD::OR, dl, VT, Tmp8, Tmp6);
8674  Tmp4 = DAG.getNode(ISD::OR, dl, VT, Tmp4, Tmp2);
8675  return DAG.getNode(ISD::OR, dl, VT, Tmp8, Tmp4);
8676  }
8677 }
8678 
8679 SDValue TargetLowering::expandVPBSWAP(SDNode *N, SelectionDAG &DAG) const {
8680  SDLoc dl(N);
8681  EVT VT = N->getValueType(0);
8682  SDValue Op = N->getOperand(0);
8683  SDValue Mask = N->getOperand(1);
8684  SDValue EVL = N->getOperand(2);
8685 
8686  if (!VT.isSimple())
8687  return SDValue();
8688 
8689  EVT SHVT = getShiftAmountTy(VT, DAG.getDataLayout());
8690  SDValue Tmp1, Tmp2, Tmp3, Tmp4, Tmp5, Tmp6, Tmp7, Tmp8;
8691  switch (VT.getSimpleVT().getScalarType().SimpleTy) {
8692  default:
8693  return SDValue();
8694  case MVT::i16:
8695  Tmp1 = DAG.getNode(ISD::VP_SHL, dl, VT, Op, DAG.getConstant(8, dl, SHVT),
8696  Mask, EVL);
8697  Tmp2 = DAG.getNode(ISD::VP_LSHR, dl, VT, Op, DAG.getConstant(8, dl, SHVT),
8698  Mask, EVL);
8699  return DAG.getNode(ISD::VP_OR, dl, VT, Tmp1, Tmp2, Mask, EVL);
8700  case MVT::i32:
8701  Tmp4 = DAG.getNode(ISD::VP_SHL, dl, VT, Op, DAG.getConstant(24, dl, SHVT),
8702  Mask, EVL);
8703  Tmp3 = DAG.getNode(ISD::VP_AND, dl, VT, Op, DAG.getConstant(0xFF00, dl, VT),
8704  Mask, EVL);
8705  Tmp3 = DAG.getNode(ISD::VP_SHL, dl, VT, Tmp3, DAG.getConstant(8, dl, SHVT),
8706  Mask, EVL);
8707  Tmp2 = DAG.getNode(ISD::VP_LSHR, dl, VT, Op, DAG.getConstant(8, dl, SHVT),
8708  Mask, EVL);
8709  Tmp2 = DAG.getNode(ISD::VP_AND, dl, VT, Tmp2,
8710  DAG.getConstant(0xFF00, dl, VT), Mask, EVL);
8711  Tmp1 = DAG.getNode(ISD::VP_LSHR, dl, VT, Op, DAG.getConstant(24, dl, SHVT),
8712  Mask, EVL);
8713  Tmp4 = DAG.getNode(ISD::VP_OR, dl, VT, Tmp4, Tmp3, Mask, EVL);
8714  Tmp2 = DAG.getNode(ISD::VP_OR, dl, VT, Tmp2, Tmp1, Mask, EVL);
8715  return DAG.getNode(ISD::VP_OR, dl, VT, Tmp4, Tmp2, Mask, EVL);
8716  case MVT::i64:
8717  Tmp8 = DAG.getNode(ISD::VP_SHL, dl, VT, Op, DAG.getConstant(56, dl, SHVT),
8718  Mask, EVL);
8719  Tmp7 = DAG.getNode(ISD::VP_AND, dl, VT, Op,
8720  DAG.getConstant(255ULL << 8, dl, VT), Mask, EVL);
8721  Tmp7 = DAG.getNode(ISD::VP_SHL, dl, VT, Tmp7, DAG.getConstant(40, dl, SHVT),
8722  Mask, EVL);
8723  Tmp6 = DAG.getNode(ISD::VP_AND, dl, VT, Op,
8724  DAG.getConstant(255ULL << 16, dl, VT), Mask, EVL);
8725  Tmp6 = DAG.getNode(ISD::VP_SHL, dl, VT, Tmp6, DAG.getConstant(24, dl, SHVT),
8726  Mask, EVL);
8727  Tmp5 = DAG.getNode(ISD::VP_AND, dl, VT, Op,
8728  DAG.getConstant(255ULL << 24, dl, VT), Mask, EVL);
8729  Tmp5 = DAG.getNode(ISD::VP_SHL, dl, VT, Tmp5, DAG.getConstant(8, dl, SHVT),
8730  Mask, EVL);
8731  Tmp4 = DAG.getNode(ISD::VP_LSHR, dl, VT, Op, DAG.getConstant(8, dl, SHVT),
8732  Mask, EVL);
8733  Tmp4 = DAG.getNode(ISD::VP_AND, dl, VT, Tmp4,
8734  DAG.getConstant(255ULL << 24, dl, VT), Mask, EVL);
8735  Tmp3 = DAG.getNode(ISD::VP_LSHR, dl, VT, Op, DAG.getConstant(24, dl, SHVT),
8736  Mask, EVL);
8737  Tmp3 = DAG.getNode(ISD::VP_AND, dl, VT, Tmp3,
8738  DAG.getConstant(255ULL << 16, dl, VT), Mask, EVL);
8739  Tmp2 = DAG.getNode(ISD::VP_LSHR, dl, VT, Op, DAG.getConstant(40, dl, SHVT),
8740  Mask, EVL);
8741  Tmp2 = DAG.getNode(ISD::VP_AND, dl, VT, Tmp2,
8742  DAG.getConstant(255ULL << 8, dl, VT), Mask, EVL);
8743  Tmp1 = DAG.getNode(ISD::VP_LSHR, dl, VT, Op, DAG.getConstant(56, dl, SHVT),
8744  Mask, EVL);
8745  Tmp8 = DAG.getNode(ISD::VP_OR, dl, VT, Tmp8, Tmp7, Mask, EVL);
8746  Tmp6 = DAG.getNode(ISD::VP_OR, dl, VT, Tmp6, Tmp5, Mask, EVL);
8747  Tmp4 = DAG.getNode(ISD::VP_OR, dl, VT, Tmp4, Tmp3, Mask, EVL);
8748  Tmp2 = DAG.getNode(ISD::VP_OR, dl, VT, Tmp2, Tmp1, Mask, EVL);
8749  Tmp8 = DAG.getNode(ISD::VP_OR, dl, VT, Tmp8, Tmp6, Mask, EVL);
8750  Tmp4 = DAG.getNode(ISD::VP_OR, dl, VT, Tmp4, Tmp2, Mask, EVL);
8751  return DAG.getNode(ISD::VP_OR, dl, VT, Tmp8, Tmp4, Mask, EVL);
8752  }
8753 }
8754 
8755 SDValue TargetLowering::expandBITREVERSE(SDNode *N, SelectionDAG &DAG) const {
8756  SDLoc dl(N);
8757  EVT VT = N->getValueType(0);
8758  SDValue Op = N->getOperand(0);
8759  EVT SHVT = getShiftAmountTy(VT, DAG.getDataLayout());
8760  unsigned Sz = VT.getScalarSizeInBits();
8761 
8762  SDValue Tmp, Tmp2, Tmp3;
8763 
8764  // If we can, perform BSWAP first and then the mask+swap the i4, then i2
8765  // and finally the i1 pairs.
8766  // TODO: We can easily support i4/i2 legal types if any target ever does.
8767  if (Sz >= 8 && isPowerOf2_32(Sz)) {
8768  // Create the masks - repeating the pattern every byte.
8769  APInt Mask4 = APInt::getSplat(Sz, APInt(8, 0x0F));
8770  APInt Mask2 = APInt::getSplat(Sz, APInt(8, 0x33));
8771  APInt Mask1 = APInt::getSplat(Sz, APInt(8, 0x55));
8772 
8773  // BSWAP if the type is wider than a single byte.
8774  Tmp = (Sz > 8 ? DAG.getNode(ISD::BSWAP, dl, VT, Op) : Op);
8775 
8776  // swap i4: ((V >> 4) & 0x0F) | ((V & 0x0F) << 4)
8777  Tmp2 = DAG.getNode(ISD::SRL, dl, VT, Tmp, DAG.getConstant(4, dl, SHVT));
8778  Tmp2 = DAG.getNode(ISD::AND, dl, VT, Tmp2, DAG.getConstant(Mask4, dl, VT));
8779  Tmp3 = DAG.getNode(ISD::AND, dl, VT, Tmp, DAG.getConstant(Mask4, dl, VT));
8780  Tmp3 = DAG.getNode(ISD::SHL, dl, VT, Tmp3, DAG.getConstant(4, dl, SHVT));
8781  Tmp = DAG.getNode(ISD::OR, dl, VT, Tmp2, Tmp3);
8782 
8783  // swap i2: ((V >> 2) & 0x33) | ((V & 0x33) << 2)
8784  Tmp2 = DAG.getNode(ISD::SRL, dl, VT, Tmp, DAG.getConstant(2, dl, SHVT));
8785  Tmp2 = DAG.getNode(ISD::AND, dl, VT, Tmp2, DAG.getConstant(Mask2, dl, VT));
8786  Tmp3 = DAG.getNode(ISD::AND, dl, VT, Tmp, DAG.getConstant(Mask2, dl, VT));
8787  Tmp3 = DAG.getNode(ISD::SHL, dl, VT, Tmp3, DAG.getConstant(2, dl, SHVT));
8788  Tmp = DAG.getNode(ISD::OR, dl, VT, Tmp2, Tmp3);
8789 
8790  // swap i1: ((V >> 1) & 0x55) | ((V & 0x55) << 1)
8791  Tmp2 = DAG.getNode(ISD::SRL, dl, VT, Tmp, DAG.getConstant(1, dl, SHVT));
8792  Tmp2 = DAG.getNode(ISD::AND, dl, VT, Tmp2, DAG.getConstant(Mask1, dl, VT));
8793  Tmp3 = DAG.getNode(ISD::AND, dl, VT, Tmp, DAG.getConstant(Mask1, dl, VT));
8794  Tmp3 = DAG.getNode(ISD::SHL, dl, VT, Tmp3, DAG.getConstant(1, dl, SHVT));
8795  Tmp = DAG.getNode(ISD::OR, dl, VT, Tmp2, Tmp3);
8796  return Tmp;
8797  }
8798 
8799  Tmp = DAG.getConstant(0, dl, VT);
8800  for (unsigned I = 0, J = Sz-1; I < Sz; ++I, --J) {
8801  if (I < J)
8802  Tmp2 =
8803  DAG.getNode(ISD::SHL, dl, VT, Op, DAG.getConstant(J - I, dl, SHVT));
8804  else
8805  Tmp2 =
8806  DAG.getNode(ISD::SRL, dl, VT, Op, DAG.getConstant(I - J, dl, SHVT));
8807 
8808  APInt Shift(Sz, 1);
8809  Shift <<= J;
8810  Tmp2 = DAG.getNode(ISD::AND, dl, VT, Tmp2, DAG.getConstant(Shift, dl, VT));
8811  Tmp = DAG.getNode(ISD::OR, dl, VT, Tmp, Tmp2);
8812  }
8813 
8814  return Tmp;
8815 }
8816 
8817 SDValue TargetLowering::expandVPBITREVERSE(SDNode *N, SelectionDAG &DAG) const {
8818  assert(N->getOpcode() == ISD::VP_BITREVERSE);
8819 
8820  SDLoc dl(N);
8821  EVT VT = N->getValueType(0);
8822  SDValue Op = N->getOperand(0);
8823  SDValue Mask = N->getOperand(1);
8824  SDValue EVL = N->getOperand(2);
8825  EVT SHVT = getShiftAmountTy(VT, DAG.getDataLayout());
8826  unsigned Sz = VT.getScalarSizeInBits();
8827 
8828  SDValue Tmp, Tmp2, Tmp3;
8829 
8830  // If we can, perform BSWAP first and then the mask+swap the i4, then i2
8831  // and finally the i1 pairs.
8832  // TODO: We can easily support i4/i2 legal types if any target ever does.
8833  if (Sz >= 8 && isPowerOf2_32(Sz)) {
8834  // Create the masks - repeating the pattern every byte.
8835  APInt Mask4 = APInt::getSplat(Sz, APInt(8, 0x0F));
8836  APInt Mask2 = APInt::getSplat(Sz, APInt(8, 0x33));
8837  APInt Mask1 = APInt::getSplat(Sz, APInt(8, 0x55));
8838 
8839  // BSWAP if the type is wider than a single byte.
8840  Tmp = (Sz > 8 ? DAG.getNode(ISD::VP_BSWAP, dl, VT, Op, Mask, EVL) : Op);
8841 
8842  // swap i4: ((V >> 4) & 0x0F) | ((V & 0x0F) << 4)
8843  Tmp2 = DAG.getNode(ISD::VP_LSHR, dl, VT, Tmp, DAG.getConstant(4, dl, SHVT),
8844  Mask, EVL);
8845  Tmp2 = DAG.getNode(ISD::VP_AND, dl, VT, Tmp2,
8846  DAG.getConstant(Mask4, dl, VT), Mask, EVL);
8847  Tmp3 = DAG.getNode(ISD::VP_AND, dl, VT, Tmp, DAG.getConstant(Mask4, dl, VT),
8848  Mask, EVL);
8849  Tmp3 = DAG.getNode(ISD::VP_SHL, dl, VT, Tmp3, DAG.getConstant(4, dl, SHVT),
8850  Mask, EVL);
8851  Tmp = DAG.getNode(ISD::VP_OR, dl, VT, Tmp2, Tmp3, Mask, EVL);
8852 
8853  // swap i2: ((V >> 2) & 0x33) | ((V & 0x33) << 2)
8854  Tmp2 = DAG.getNode(ISD::VP_LSHR, dl, VT, Tmp, DAG.getConstant(2, dl, SHVT),
8855  Mask, EVL);
8856  Tmp2 = DAG.getNode(ISD::VP_AND, dl, VT, Tmp2,
8857  DAG.getConstant(Mask2, dl, VT), Mask, EVL);
8858  Tmp3 = DAG.getNode(ISD::VP_AND, dl, VT, Tmp, DAG.getConstant(Mask2, dl, VT),
8859  Mask, EVL);
8860  Tmp3 = DAG.getNode(ISD::VP_SHL, dl, VT, Tmp3, DAG.getConstant(2, dl, SHVT),
8861  Mask, EVL);
8862  Tmp = DAG.getNode(ISD::VP_OR, dl, VT, Tmp2, Tmp3, Mask, EVL);
8863 
8864  // swap i1: ((V >> 1) & 0x55) | ((V & 0x55) << 1)
8865  Tmp2 = DAG.getNode(ISD::VP_LSHR, dl, VT, Tmp, DAG.getConstant(1, dl, SHVT),
8866  Mask, EVL);
8867  Tmp2 = DAG.getNode(ISD::VP_AND, dl, VT, Tmp2,
8868  DAG.getConstant(Mask1, dl, VT), Mask, EVL);
8869  Tmp3 = DAG.getNode(ISD::VP_AND, dl, VT, Tmp, DAG.getConstant(Mask1, dl, VT),
8870  Mask, EVL);
8871  Tmp3 = DAG.getNode(ISD::VP_SHL, dl, VT, Tmp3, DAG.getConstant(1, dl, SHVT),
8872  Mask, EVL);
8873  Tmp = DAG.getNode(ISD::VP_OR, dl, VT, Tmp2, Tmp3, Mask, EVL);
8874  return Tmp;
8875  }
8876  return SDValue();
8877 }
8878 
8879 std::pair<SDValue, SDValue>
8880 TargetLowering::scalarizeVectorLoad(LoadSDNode *LD,
8881  SelectionDAG &DAG) const {
8882  SDLoc SL(LD);
8883  SDValue Chain = LD->getChain();
8884  SDValue BasePTR = LD->getBasePtr();
8885  EVT SrcVT = LD->getMemoryVT();
8886  EVT DstVT = LD->getValueType(0);
8887  ISD::LoadExtType ExtType = LD->getExtensionType();
8888 
8889  if (SrcVT.isScalableVector())
8890  report_fatal_error("Cannot scalarize scalable vector loads");
8891 
8892  unsigned NumElem = SrcVT.getVectorNumElements();
8893 
8894  EVT SrcEltVT = SrcVT.getScalarType();
8895  EVT DstEltVT = DstVT.getScalarType();
8896 
8897  // A vector must always be stored in memory as-is, i.e. without any padding
8898  // between the elements, since various code depend on it, e.g. in the
8899  // handling of a bitcast of a vector type to int, which may be done with a
8900  // vector store followed by an integer load. A vector that does not have
8901  // elements that are byte-sized must therefore be stored as an integer
8902  // built out of the extracted vector elements.
8903  if (!SrcEltVT.isByteSized()) {
8904  unsigned NumLoadBits = SrcVT.getStoreSizeInBits();
8905  EVT LoadVT = EVT::getIntegerVT(*DAG.getContext(), NumLoadBits);
8906 
8907  unsigned NumSrcBits = SrcVT.getSizeInBits();
8908  EVT SrcIntVT = EVT::getIntegerVT(*DAG.getContext(), NumSrcBits);
8909 
8910  unsigned SrcEltBits = SrcEltVT.getSizeInBits();
8911  SDValue SrcEltBitMask = DAG.getConstant(
8912  APInt::getLowBitsSet(NumLoadBits, SrcEltBits), SL, LoadVT);
8913 
8914  // Load the whole vector and avoid masking off the top bits as it makes
8915  // the codegen worse.
8916  SDValue Load =
8917  DAG.getExtLoad(ISD::EXTLOAD, SL, LoadVT, Chain, BasePTR,
8918  LD->getPointerInfo(), SrcIntVT, LD->getOriginalAlign(),
8919  LD->getMemOperand()->getFlags(), LD->getAAInfo());
8920 
8921  SmallVector<SDValue, 8> Vals;
8922  for (unsigned Idx = 0; Idx < NumElem; ++Idx) {
8923  unsigned ShiftIntoIdx =
8924  (DAG.getDataLayout().isBigEndian() ? (NumElem - 1) - Idx : Idx);
8925  SDValue ShiftAmount =
8926  DAG.getShiftAmountConstant(ShiftIntoIdx * SrcEltVT.getSizeInBits(),
8927  LoadVT, SL, /*LegalTypes=*/false);
8928  SDValue ShiftedElt = DAG.getNode(ISD::SRL, SL, LoadVT, Load, ShiftAmount);
8929  SDValue Elt =
8930  DAG.getNode(ISD::AND, SL, LoadVT, ShiftedElt, SrcEltBitMask);
8931  SDValue Scalar = DAG.getNode(ISD::TRUNCATE, SL, SrcEltVT, Elt);
8932 
8933  if (ExtType != ISD::NON_EXTLOAD) {
8934  unsigned ExtendOp = ISD::getExtForLoadExtType(false, ExtType);
8935  Scalar = DAG.getNode(ExtendOp, SL, DstEltVT, Scalar);
8936  }
8937 
8938  Vals.push_back(Scalar);
8939  }
8940 
8941  SDValue Value = DAG.getBuildVector(DstVT, SL, Vals);
8942  return std::make_pair(Value, Load.getValue(1));
8943  }
8944 
8945  unsigned Stride = SrcEltVT.getSizeInBits() / 8;
8946  assert(SrcEltVT.isByteSized());
8947 
8948  SmallVector<SDValue, 8> Vals;
8949  SmallVector<SDValue, 8> LoadChains;
8950 
8951  for (unsigned Idx = 0; Idx < NumElem; ++Idx) {
8952  SDValue ScalarLoad =
8953  DAG.getExtLoad(ExtType, SL, DstEltVT, Chain, BasePTR,
8954  LD->getPointerInfo().getWithOffset(Idx * Stride),
8955  SrcEltVT, LD->getOriginalAlign(),
8956  LD->getMemOperand()->getFlags(), LD->getAAInfo());
8957 
8958  BasePTR = DAG.getObjectPtrOffset(SL, BasePTR, TypeSize::Fixed(Stride));
8959 
8960  Vals.push_back(ScalarLoad.getValue(0));
8961  LoadChains.push_back(ScalarLoad.getValue(1));
8962  }
8963 
8964  SDValue NewChain = DAG.getNode(ISD::TokenFactor, SL, MVT::Other, LoadChains);
8965  SDValue Value = DAG.getBuildVector(DstVT, SL, Vals);
8966 
8967  return std::make_pair(Value, NewChain);
8968 }
8969 
8970 SDValue TargetLowering::scalarizeVectorStore(StoreSDNode *ST,
8971  SelectionDAG &DAG) const {
8972  SDLoc SL(ST);
8973 
8974  SDValue Chain = ST->getChain();
8975  SDValue BasePtr = ST->getBasePtr();
8976  SDValue Value = ST->getValue();
8977  EVT StVT = ST->getMemoryVT();
8978 
8979  if (StVT.isScalableVector())
8980  report_fatal_error("Cannot scalarize scalable vector stores");
8981 
8982  // The type of the data we want to save
8983  EVT RegVT = Value.getValueType();
8984  EVT RegSclVT = RegVT.getScalarType();
8985 
8986  // The type of data as saved in memory.
8987  EVT MemSclVT = StVT.getScalarType();
8988 
8989  unsigned NumElem = StVT.getVectorNumElements();
8990 
8991  // A vector must always be stored in memory as-is, i.e. without any padding
8992  // between the elements, since various code depend on it, e.g. in the
8993  // handling of a bitcast of a vector type to int, which may be done with a
8994  // vector store followed by an integer load. A vector that does not have
8995  // elements that are byte-sized must therefore be stored as an integer
8996  // built out of the extracted vector elements.
8997  if (!MemSclVT.isByteSized()) {
8998  unsigned NumBits = StVT.getSizeInBits();
8999  EVT IntVT = EVT::getIntegerVT(*DAG.getContext(), NumBits);
9000 
9001  SDValue CurrVal = DAG.getConstant(0, SL, IntVT);
9002 
9003  for (unsigned Idx = 0; Idx < NumElem; ++Idx) {
9004  SDValue Elt = DAG.getNode(ISD::EXTRACT_VECTOR_ELT, SL, RegSclVT, Value,
9005  DAG.getVectorIdxConstant(Idx, SL));
9006  SDValue Trunc = DAG.getNode(ISD::TRUNCATE, SL, MemSclVT, Elt);
9007  SDValue ExtElt = DAG.getNode(ISD::ZERO_EXTEND, SL, IntVT, Trunc);
9008  unsigned ShiftIntoIdx =
9009  (DAG.getDataLayout().isBigEndian() ? (NumElem - 1) - Idx : Idx);
9010  SDValue ShiftAmount =
9011  DAG.getConstant(ShiftIntoIdx * MemSclVT.getSizeInBits(), SL, IntVT);
9012  SDValue ShiftedElt =
9013  DAG.getNode(ISD::SHL, SL, IntVT, ExtElt, ShiftAmount);
9014  CurrVal = DAG.getNode(ISD::OR, SL, IntVT, CurrVal, ShiftedElt);
9015  }
9016 
9017  return DAG.getStore(Chain, SL, CurrVal, BasePtr, ST->getPointerInfo(),
9018  ST->getOriginalAlign(), ST->getMemOperand()->getFlags(),
9019  ST->getAAInfo());
9020  }
9021 
9022  // Store Stride in bytes
9023  unsigned Stride = MemSclVT.getSizeInBits() / 8;
9024  assert(Stride && "Zero stride!");
9025  // Extract each of the elements from the original vector and save them into
9026  // memory individually.
9027  SmallVector<SDValue, 8> Stores;
9028  for (unsigned Idx = 0; Idx < NumElem; ++Idx) {
9029  SDValue Elt = DAG.getNode(ISD::EXTRACT_VECTOR_ELT, SL, RegSclVT, Value,
9030  DAG.getVectorIdxConstant(Idx, SL));
9031 
9032  SDValue Ptr =
9033  DAG.getObjectPtrOffset(SL, BasePtr, TypeSize::Fixed(Idx * Stride));
9034 
9035  // This scalar TruncStore may be illegal, but we legalize it later.
9036  SDValue Store = DAG.getTruncStore(
9037  Chain, SL, Elt, Ptr, ST->getPointerInfo().getWithOffset(Idx * Stride),
9038  MemSclVT, ST->getOriginalAlign(), ST->getMemOperand()->getFlags(),
9039  ST->getAAInfo());
9040 
9041  Stores.push_back(Store);
9042  }
9043 
9044  return DAG.getNode(ISD::TokenFactor, SL, MVT::Other, Stores);
9045 }
9046 
9047 std::pair<SDValue, SDValue>
9048 TargetLowering::expandUnalignedLoad(LoadSDNode *LD, SelectionDAG &DAG) const {
9049  assert(LD->getAddressingMode() == ISD::UNINDEXED &&
9050  "unaligned indexed loads not implemented!");
9051  SDValue Chain = LD->getChain();
9052  SDValue Ptr = LD->getBasePtr();
9053  EVT VT = LD->getValueType(0);
9054  EVT LoadedVT = LD->getMemoryVT();
9055  SDLoc dl(LD);
9056  auto &MF = DAG.getMachineFunction();
9057 
9058  if (VT.isFloatingPoint() || VT.isVector()) {
9059  EVT intVT = EVT::getIntegerVT(*DAG.getContext(), LoadedVT.getSizeInBits());
9060  if (isTypeLegal(intVT) && isTypeLegal(LoadedVT)) {
9061  if (!isOperationLegalOrCustom(ISD::LOAD, intVT) &&
9062  LoadedVT.isVector()) {
9063  // Scalarize the load and let the individual components be handled.
9064  return scalarizeVectorLoad(LD, DAG);
9065  }
9066 
9067  // Expand to a (misaligned) integer load of the same size,
9068  // then bitconvert to floating point or vector.
9069  SDValue newLoad = DAG.getLoad(intVT, dl, Chain, Ptr,
9070  LD->getMemOperand());
9071  SDValue Result = DAG.getNode(ISD::BITCAST, dl, LoadedVT, newLoad);
9072  if (LoadedVT != VT)
9073  Result = DAG.getNode(VT.isFloatingPoint() ? ISD::FP_EXTEND :
9074  ISD::ANY_EXTEND, dl, VT, Result);
9075 
9076  return std::make_pair(Result, newLoad.getValue(1));
9077  }
9078 
9079  // Copy the value to a (aligned) stack slot using (unaligned) integer
9080  // loads and stores, then do a (aligned) load from the stack slot.
9081  MVT RegVT = getRegisterType(*DAG.getContext(), intVT);
9082  unsigned LoadedBytes = LoadedVT.getStoreSize();
9083  unsigned RegBytes = RegVT.getSizeInBits() / 8;
9084  unsigned NumRegs = (LoadedBytes + RegBytes - 1) / RegBytes;
9085 
9086  // Make sure the stack slot is also aligned for the register type.
9087  SDValue StackBase = DAG.CreateStackTemporary(LoadedVT, RegVT);
9088  auto FrameIndex = cast<FrameIndexSDNode>(StackBase.getNode())->getIndex();
9089  SmallVector<SDValue, 8> Stores;
9090  SDValue StackPtr = StackBase;
9091  unsigned Offset = 0;
9092 
9093  EVT PtrVT = Ptr.getValueType();
9094  EVT StackPtrVT = StackPtr.getValueType();
9095 
9096  SDValue PtrIncrement = DAG.getConstant(RegBytes, dl, PtrVT);
9097  SDValue StackPtrIncrement = DAG.getConstant(RegBytes, dl, StackPtrVT);
9098 
9099  // Do all but one copies using the full register width.
9100  for (unsigned i = 1; i < NumRegs; i++) {
9101  // Load one integer register's worth from the original location.
9102  SDValue Load = DAG.getLoad(
9103  RegVT, dl, Chain, Ptr, LD->getPointerInfo().getWithOffset(Offset),
9104  LD->getOriginalAlign(), LD->getMemOperand()->getFlags(),
9105  LD->getAAInfo());
9106  // Follow the load with a store to the stack slot. Remember the store.
9107  Stores.push_back(DAG.getStore(
9108  Load.getValue(1), dl, Load, StackPtr,
9109  MachinePointerInfo::getFixedStack(MF, FrameIndex, Offset)));
9110  // Increment the pointers.
9111  Offset += RegBytes;
9112 
9113  Ptr = DAG.getObjectPtrOffset(dl, Ptr, PtrIncrement);
9114  StackPtr = DAG.getObjectPtrOffset(dl, StackPtr, StackPtrIncrement);
9115  }
9116 
9117  // The last copy may be partial. Do an extending load.
9118  EVT MemVT = EVT::getIntegerVT(*DAG.getContext(),
9119  8 * (LoadedBytes - Offset));
9120  SDValue Load =
9121  DAG.getExtLoad(ISD::EXTLOAD, dl, RegVT, Chain, Ptr,
9122  LD->getPointerInfo().getWithOffset(Offset), MemVT,
9123  LD->getOriginalAlign(), LD->getMemOperand()->getFlags(),
9124  LD->getAAInfo());
9125  // Follow the load with a store to the stack slot. Remember the store.
9126  // On big-endian machines this requires a truncating store to ensure
9127  // that the bits end up in the right place.
9128  Stores.push_back(DAG.getTruncStore(
9129  Load.getValue(1), dl, Load, StackPtr,
9130  MachinePointerInfo::getFixedStack(MF, FrameIndex, Offset), MemVT));
9131 
9132  // The order of the stores doesn't matter - say it with a TokenFactor.
9133  SDValue TF = DAG.getNode(ISD::TokenFactor, dl, MVT::Other, Stores);
9134 
9135  // Finally, perform the original load only redirected to the stack slot.
9136  Load = DAG.getExtLoad(LD->getExtensionType(), dl, VT, TF, StackBase,
9137  MachinePointerInfo::getFixedStack(MF, FrameIndex, 0),
9138  LoadedVT);
9139 
9140  // Callers expect a MERGE_VALUES node.
9141  return std::make_pair(Load, TF);
9142  }
9143 
9144  assert(LoadedVT.isInteger() && !LoadedVT.isVector() &&
9145  "Unaligned load of unsupported type.");
9146 
9147  // Compute the new VT that is half the size of the old one. This is an
9148  // integer MVT.
9149  unsigned NumBits = LoadedVT.getSizeInBits();
9150  EVT NewLoadedVT;
9151  NewLoadedVT = EVT::getIntegerVT(*DAG.getContext(), NumBits/2);
9152  NumBits >>= 1;
9153 
9154  Align Alignment = LD->getOriginalAlign();
9155  unsigned IncrementSize = NumBits / 8;
9156  ISD::LoadExtType HiExtType = LD->getExtensionType();
9157 
9158  // If the original load is NON_EXTLOAD, the hi part load must be ZEXTLOAD.
9159  if (HiExtType == ISD::NON_EXTLOAD)
9160  HiExtType = ISD::ZEXTLOAD;
9161 
9162  // Load the value in two parts
9163  SDValue Lo, Hi;
9164  if (DAG.getDataLayout().isLittleEndian()) {
9165  Lo = DAG.getExtLoad(ISD::ZEXTLOAD, dl, VT, Chain, Ptr, LD->getPointerInfo(),
9166  NewLoadedVT, Alignment, LD->getMemOperand()->getFlags(),
9167  LD->getAAInfo());
9168 
9169  Ptr = DAG.getObjectPtrOffset(dl, Ptr, TypeSize::Fixed(IncrementSize));
9170  Hi = DAG.getExtLoad(HiExtType, dl, VT, Chain, Ptr,
9171  LD->getPointerInfo().getWithOffset(IncrementSize),
9172  NewLoadedVT, Alignment, LD->getMemOperand()->getFlags(),
9173  LD->getAAInfo());
9174  } else {
9175  Hi = DAG.getExtLoad(HiExtType, dl, VT, Chain, Ptr, LD->getPointerInfo(),
9176  NewLoadedVT, Alignment, LD->getMemOperand()->getFlags(),
9177  LD->getAAInfo());
9178 
9179  Ptr = DAG.getObjectPtrOffset(dl, Ptr, TypeSize::Fixed(IncrementSize));
9180  Lo = DAG.getExtLoad(ISD::ZEXTLOAD, dl, VT, Chain, Ptr,
9181  LD->getPointerInfo().getWithOffset(IncrementSize),
9182  NewLoadedVT, Alignment, LD->getMemOperand()->getFlags(),
9183  LD->getAAInfo());
9184  }
9185 
9186  // aggregate the two parts
9187  SDValue ShiftAmount =
9188  DAG.getConstant(NumBits, dl, getShiftAmountTy(Hi.getValueType(),
9189  DAG.getDataLayout()));
9190  SDValue Result = DAG.getNode(ISD::SHL, dl, VT, Hi, ShiftAmount);
9191  Result = DAG.getNode(ISD::OR, dl, VT, Result, Lo);
9192 
9193  SDValue TF = DAG.getNode(ISD::TokenFactor, dl, MVT::Other, Lo.getValue(1),
9194  Hi.getValue(1));
9195 
9196  return std::make_pair(Result, TF);
9197 }
9198 
9199 SDValue TargetLowering::expandUnalignedStore(StoreSDNode *ST,
9200  SelectionDAG &DAG) const {
9201  assert(ST->getAddressingMode() == ISD::UNINDEXED &&
9202  "unaligned indexed stores not implemented!");
9203  SDValue Chain = ST->getChain();
9204  SDValue Ptr = ST->getBasePtr();
9205  SDValue Val = ST->getValue();
9206  EVT VT = Val.getValueType();
9207  Align Alignment = ST->getOriginalAlign();
9208  auto &MF = DAG.getMachineFunction();
9209  EVT StoreMemVT = ST->getMemoryVT();
9210 
9211  SDLoc dl(ST);
9212  if (StoreMemVT.isFloatingPoint() || StoreMemVT.isVector()) {
9213  EVT intVT = EVT::getIntegerVT(*DAG.getContext(), VT.getSizeInBits());
9214  if (isTypeLegal(intVT)) {
9215  if (!isOperationLegalOrCustom(ISD::STORE, intVT) &&
9216  StoreMemVT.isVector()) {
9217  // Scalarize the store and let the individual components be handled.
9218  SDValue Result = scalarizeVectorStore(ST, DAG);
9219  return Result;
9220  }
9221  // Expand to a bitconvert of the value to the integer type of the
9222  // same size, then a (misaligned) int store.
9223  // FIXME: Does not handle truncating floating point stores!
9224  SDValue Result = DAG.getNode(ISD::BITCAST, dl, intVT, Val);
9225  Result = DAG.getStore(Chain, dl, Result, Ptr, ST->getPointerInfo(),
9226  Alignment, ST->getMemOperand()->getFlags());
9227  return Result;
9228  }
9229  // Do a (aligned) store to a stack slot, then copy from the stack slot
9230  // to the final destination using (unaligned) integer loads and stores.
9231  MVT RegVT = getRegisterType(
9232  *DAG.getContext(),
9233  EVT::getIntegerVT(*DAG.getContext(), StoreMemVT.getSizeInBits()));
9234  EVT PtrVT = Ptr.getValueType();
9235  unsigned StoredBytes = StoreMemVT.getStoreSize();
9236  unsigned RegBytes = RegVT.getSizeInBits() / 8;
9237  unsigned NumRegs = (StoredBytes + RegBytes - 1) / RegBytes;
9238 
9239  // Make sure the stack slot is also aligned for the register type.
9240  SDValue StackPtr = DAG.CreateStackTemporary(StoreMemVT, RegVT);
9241  auto FrameIndex = cast<FrameIndexSDNode>(StackPtr.getNode())->getIndex();
9242 
9243  // Perform the original store, only redirected to the stack slot.
9244  SDValue Store = DAG.getTruncStore(
9245  Chain, dl, Val, StackPtr,
9246  MachinePointerInfo::getFixedStack(MF, FrameIndex, 0), StoreMemVT);
9247 
9248  EVT StackPtrVT = StackPtr.getValueType();
9249 
9250  SDValue PtrIncrement = DAG.getConstant(RegBytes, dl, PtrVT);
9251  SDValue StackPtrIncrement = DAG.getConstant(RegBytes, dl, StackPtrVT);
9252  SmallVector<SDValue, 8> Stores;
9253  unsigned Offset = 0;
9254 
9255  // Do all but one copies using the full register width.
9256  for (unsigned i = 1; i < NumRegs; i++) {
9257  // Load one integer register's worth from the stack slot.
9258  SDValue Load = DAG.getLoad(
9259  RegVT, dl, Store, StackPtr,
9260  MachinePointerInfo::getFixedStack(MF, FrameIndex, Offset));
9261  // Store it to the final location. Remember the store.
