9262  Stores.push_back(DAG.getStore(Load.getValue(1), dl, Load, Ptr,
9263  ST->getPointerInfo().getWithOffset(Offset),
9264  ST->getOriginalAlign(),
9265  ST->getMemOperand()->getFlags()));
9266  // Increment the pointers.
9267  Offset += RegBytes;
9268  StackPtr = DAG.getObjectPtrOffset(dl, StackPtr, StackPtrIncrement);
9269  Ptr = DAG.getObjectPtrOffset(dl, Ptr, PtrIncrement);
9270  }
9271 
9272  // The last store may be partial. Do a truncating store. On big-endian
9273  // machines this requires an extending load from the stack slot to ensure
9274  // that the bits are in the right place.
9275  EVT LoadMemVT =
9276  EVT::getIntegerVT(*DAG.getContext(), 8 * (StoredBytes - Offset));
9277 
9278  // Load from the stack slot.
9279  SDValue Load = DAG.getExtLoad(
9280  ISD::EXTLOAD, dl, RegVT, Store, StackPtr,
9281  MachinePointerInfo::getFixedStack(MF, FrameIndex, Offset), LoadMemVT);
9282 
9283  Stores.push_back(
9284  DAG.getTruncStore(Load.getValue(1), dl, Load, Ptr,
9285  ST->getPointerInfo().getWithOffset(Offset), LoadMemVT,
9286  ST->getOriginalAlign(),
9287  ST->getMemOperand()->getFlags(), ST->getAAInfo()));
9288  // The order of the stores doesn't matter - say it with a TokenFactor.
9289  SDValue Result = DAG.getNode(ISD::TokenFactor, dl, MVT::Other, Stores);
9290  return Result;
9291  }
9292 
9293  assert(StoreMemVT.isInteger() && !StoreMemVT.isVector() &&
9294  "Unaligned store of unknown type.");
9295  // Get the half-size VT
9296  EVT NewStoredVT = StoreMemVT.getHalfSizedIntegerVT(*DAG.getContext());
9297  unsigned NumBits = NewStoredVT.getFixedSizeInBits();
9298  unsigned IncrementSize = NumBits / 8;
9299 
9300  // Divide the stored value in two parts.
9301  SDValue ShiftAmount = DAG.getConstant(
9302  NumBits, dl, getShiftAmountTy(Val.getValueType(), DAG.getDataLayout()));
9303  SDValue Lo = Val;
9304  SDValue Hi = DAG.getNode(ISD::SRL, dl, VT, Val, ShiftAmount);
9305 
9306  // Store the two parts
9307  SDValue Store1, Store2;
9308  Store1 = DAG.getTruncStore(Chain, dl,
9309  DAG.getDataLayout().isLittleEndian() ? Lo : Hi,
9310  Ptr, ST->getPointerInfo(), NewStoredVT, Alignment,
9311  ST->getMemOperand()->getFlags());
9312 
9313  Ptr = DAG.getObjectPtrOffset(dl, Ptr, TypeSize::Fixed(IncrementSize));
9314  Store2 = DAG.getTruncStore(
9315  Chain, dl, DAG.getDataLayout().isLittleEndian() ? Hi : Lo, Ptr,
9316  ST->getPointerInfo().getWithOffset(IncrementSize), NewStoredVT, Alignment,
9317  ST->getMemOperand()->getFlags(), ST->getAAInfo());
9318 
9319  SDValue Result =
9320  DAG.getNode(ISD::TokenFactor, dl, MVT::Other, Store1, Store2);
9321  return Result;
9322 }
9323 
9324 SDValue
9325 TargetLowering::IncrementMemoryAddress(SDValue Addr, SDValue Mask,
9326  const SDLoc &DL, EVT DataVT,
9327  SelectionDAG &DAG,
9328  bool IsCompressedMemory) const {
9329  SDValue Increment;
9330  EVT AddrVT = Addr.getValueType();
9331  EVT MaskVT = Mask.getValueType();
9332  assert(DataVT.getVectorElementCount() == MaskVT.getVectorElementCount() &&
9333  "Incompatible types of Data and Mask");
9334  if (IsCompressedMemory) {
9335  if (DataVT.isScalableVector())
9336  report_fatal_error(
9337  "Cannot currently handle compressed memory with scalable vectors");
9338  // Incrementing the pointer according to number of '1's in the mask.
9339  EVT MaskIntVT = EVT::getIntegerVT(*DAG.getContext(), MaskVT.getSizeInBits());
9340  SDValue MaskInIntReg = DAG.getBitcast(MaskIntVT, Mask);
9341  if (MaskIntVT.getSizeInBits() < 32) {
9342  MaskInIntReg = DAG.getNode(ISD::ZERO_EXTEND, DL, MVT::i32, MaskInIntReg);
9343  MaskIntVT = MVT::i32;
9344  }
9345 
9346  // Count '1's with POPCNT.
9347  Increment = DAG.getNode(ISD::CTPOP, DL, MaskIntVT, MaskInIntReg);
9348  Increment = DAG.getZExtOrTrunc(Increment, DL, AddrVT);
9349  // Scale is an element size in bytes.
9350  SDValue Scale = DAG.getConstant(DataVT.getScalarSizeInBits() / 8, DL,
9351  AddrVT);
9352  Increment = DAG.getNode(ISD::MUL, DL, AddrVT, Increment, Scale);
9353  } else if (DataVT.isScalableVector()) {
9354  Increment = DAG.getVScale(DL, AddrVT,
9355  APInt(AddrVT.getFixedSizeInBits(),
9356  DataVT.getStoreSize().getKnownMinValue()));
9357  } else
9358  Increment = DAG.getConstant(DataVT.getStoreSize(), DL, AddrVT);
9359 
9360  return DAG.getNode(ISD::ADD, DL, AddrVT, Addr, Increment);
9361 }
9362 
9363 static SDValue clampDynamicVectorIndex(SelectionDAG &DAG, SDValue Idx,
9364  EVT VecVT, const SDLoc &dl,
9365  ElementCount SubEC) {
9366  assert(!(SubEC.isScalable() && VecVT.isFixedLengthVector()) &&
9367  "Cannot index a scalable vector within a fixed-width vector");
9368 
9369  unsigned NElts = VecVT.getVectorMinNumElements();
9370  unsigned NumSubElts = SubEC.getKnownMinValue();
9371  EVT IdxVT = Idx.getValueType();
9372 
9373  if (VecVT.isScalableVector() && !SubEC.isScalable()) {
9374  // If this is a constant index and we know the value plus the number of the
9375  // elements in the subvector minus one is less than the minimum number of
9376  // elements then it's safe to return Idx.
9377  if (auto *IdxCst = dyn_cast<ConstantSDNode>(Idx))
9378  if (IdxCst->getZExtValue() + (NumSubElts - 1) < NElts)
9379  return Idx;
9380  SDValue VS =
9381  DAG.getVScale(dl, IdxVT, APInt(IdxVT.getFixedSizeInBits(), NElts));
9382  unsigned SubOpcode = NumSubElts <= NElts ? ISD::SUB : ISD::USUBSAT;
9383  SDValue Sub = DAG.getNode(SubOpcode, dl, IdxVT, VS,
9384  DAG.getConstant(NumSubElts, dl, IdxVT));
9385  return DAG.getNode(ISD::UMIN, dl, IdxVT, Idx, Sub);
9386  }
9387  if (isPowerOf2_32(NElts) && NumSubElts == 1) {
9388  APInt Imm = APInt::getLowBitsSet(IdxVT.getSizeInBits(), Log2_32(NElts));
9389  return DAG.getNode(ISD::AND, dl, IdxVT, Idx,
9390  DAG.getConstant(Imm, dl, IdxVT));
9391  }
9392  unsigned MaxIndex = NumSubElts < NElts ? NElts - NumSubElts : 0;
9393  return DAG.getNode(ISD::UMIN, dl, IdxVT, Idx,
9394  DAG.getConstant(MaxIndex, dl, IdxVT));
9395 }
9396 
9397 SDValue TargetLowering::getVectorElementPointer(SelectionDAG &DAG,
9398  SDValue VecPtr, EVT VecVT,
9399  SDValue Index) const {
9400  return getVectorSubVecPointer(
9401  DAG, VecPtr, VecVT,
9402  EVT::getVectorVT(*DAG.getContext(), VecVT.getVectorElementType(), 1),
9403  Index);
9404 }
9405 
9406 SDValue TargetLowering::getVectorSubVecPointer(SelectionDAG &DAG,
9407  SDValue VecPtr, EVT VecVT,
9408  EVT SubVecVT,
9409  SDValue Index) const {
9410  SDLoc dl(Index);
9411  // Make sure the index type is big enough to compute in.
9412  Index = DAG.getZExtOrTrunc(Index, dl, VecPtr.getValueType());
9413 
9414  EVT EltVT = VecVT.getVectorElementType();
9415 
9416  // Calculate the element offset and add it to the pointer.
9417  unsigned EltSize = EltVT.getFixedSizeInBits() / 8; // FIXME: should be ABI size.
9418  assert(EltSize * 8 == EltVT.getFixedSizeInBits() &&
9419  "Converting bits to bytes lost precision");
9420  assert(SubVecVT.getVectorElementType() == EltVT &&
9421  "Sub-vector must be a vector with matching element type");
9422  Index = clampDynamicVectorIndex(DAG, Index, VecVT, dl,
9423  SubVecVT.getVectorElementCount());
9424 
9425  EVT IdxVT = Index.getValueType();
9426  if (SubVecVT.isScalableVector())
9427  Index =
9428  DAG.getNode(ISD::MUL, dl, IdxVT, Index,
9429  DAG.getVScale(dl, IdxVT, APInt(IdxVT.getSizeInBits(), 1)));
9430 
9431  Index = DAG.getNode(ISD::MUL, dl, IdxVT, Index,
9432  DAG.getConstant(EltSize, dl, IdxVT));
9433  return DAG.getMemBasePlusOffset(VecPtr, Index, dl);
9434 }
9435 
9436 //===----------------------------------------------------------------------===//
9437 // Implementation of Emulated TLS Model
9438 //===----------------------------------------------------------------------===//
9439 
9440 SDValue TargetLowering::LowerToTLSEmulatedModel(const GlobalAddressSDNode *GA,
9441  SelectionDAG &DAG) const {
9442  // Access to address of TLS varialbe xyz is lowered to a function call:
9443  // __emutls_get_address( address of global variable named "__emutls_v.xyz" )
9444  EVT PtrVT = getPointerTy(DAG.getDataLayout());
9445  PointerType *VoidPtrType = Type::getInt8PtrTy(*DAG.getContext());
9446  SDLoc dl(GA);
9447 
9448  ArgListTy Args;
9449  ArgListEntry Entry;
9450  std::string NameString = ("__emutls_v." + GA->getGlobal()->getName()).str();
9451  Module *VariableModule = const_cast<Module*>(GA->getGlobal()->getParent());
9452  StringRef EmuTlsVarName(NameString);
9453  GlobalVariable *EmuTlsVar = VariableModule->getNamedGlobal(EmuTlsVarName);
9454  assert(EmuTlsVar && "Cannot find EmuTlsVar ");
9455  Entry.Node = DAG.getGlobalAddress(EmuTlsVar, dl, PtrVT);
9456  Entry.Ty = VoidPtrType;
9457  Args.push_back(Entry);
9458 
9459  SDValue EmuTlsGetAddr = DAG.getExternalSymbol("__emutls_get_address", PtrVT);
9460 
9461  TargetLowering::CallLoweringInfo CLI(DAG);
9462  CLI.setDebugLoc(dl).setChain(DAG.getEntryNode());
9463  CLI.setLibCallee(CallingConv::C, VoidPtrType, EmuTlsGetAddr, std::move(Args));
9464  std::pair<SDValue, SDValue> CallResult = LowerCallTo(CLI);
9465 
9466  // TLSADDR will be codegen'ed as call. Inform MFI that function has calls.
9467  // At last for X86 targets, maybe good for other targets too?
9468  MachineFrameInfo &MFI = DAG.getMachineFunction().getFrameInfo();
9469  MFI.setAdjustsStack(true); // Is this only for X86 target?
9470  MFI.setHasCalls(true);
9471 
9472  assert((GA->getOffset() == 0) &&
9473  "Emulated TLS must have zero offset in GlobalAddressSDNode");
9474  return CallResult.first;
9475 }
9476 
9477 SDValue TargetLowering::lowerCmpEqZeroToCtlzSrl(SDValue Op,
9478  SelectionDAG &DAG) const {
9479  assert((Op->getOpcode() == ISD::SETCC) && "Input has to be a SETCC node.");
9480  if (!isCtlzFast())
9481  return SDValue();
9482  ISD::CondCode CC = cast<CondCodeSDNode>(Op.getOperand(2))->get();
9483  SDLoc dl(Op);
9484  if (ConstantSDNode *C = dyn_cast<ConstantSDNode>(Op.getOperand(1))) {
9485  if (C->isZero() && CC == ISD::SETEQ) {
9486  EVT VT = Op.getOperand(0).getValueType();
9487  SDValue Zext = Op.getOperand(0);
9488  if (VT.bitsLT(MVT::i32)) {
9489  VT = MVT::i32;
9490  Zext = DAG.getNode(ISD::ZERO_EXTEND, dl, VT, Op.getOperand(0));
9491  }
9492  unsigned Log2b = Log2_32(VT.getSizeInBits());
9493  SDValue Clz = DAG.getNode(ISD::CTLZ, dl, VT, Zext);
9494  SDValue Scc = DAG.getNode(ISD::SRL, dl, VT, Clz,
9495  DAG.getConstant(Log2b, dl, MVT::i32));
9496  return DAG.getNode(ISD::TRUNCATE, dl, MVT::i32, Scc);
9497  }
9498  }
9499  return SDValue();
9500 }
9501 
9502 SDValue TargetLowering::expandIntMINMAX(SDNode *Node, SelectionDAG &DAG) const {
9503  SDValue Op0 = Node->getOperand(0);
9504  SDValue Op1 = Node->getOperand(1);
9505  EVT VT = Op0.getValueType();
9506  unsigned Opcode = Node->getOpcode();
9507  SDLoc DL(Node);
9508 
9509  // umin(x,y) -> sub(x,usubsat(x,y))
9510  if (Opcode == ISD::UMIN && isOperationLegal(ISD::SUB, VT) &&
9511  isOperationLegal(ISD::USUBSAT, VT)) {
9512  return DAG.getNode(ISD::SUB, DL, VT, Op0,
9513  DAG.getNode(ISD::USUBSAT, DL, VT, Op0, Op1));
9514  }
9515 
9516  // umax(x,y) -> add(x,usubsat(y,x))
9517  if (Opcode == ISD::UMAX && isOperationLegal(ISD::ADD, VT) &&
9518  isOperationLegal(ISD::USUBSAT, VT)) {
9519  return DAG.getNode(ISD::ADD, DL, VT, Op0,
9520  DAG.getNode(ISD::USUBSAT, DL, VT, Op1, Op0));
9521  }
9522 
9523  // Expand Y = MAX(A, B) -> Y = (A > B) ? A : B
9524  ISD::CondCode CC;
9525  switch (Opcode) {
9526  default: llvm_unreachable("How did we get here?");
9527  case ISD::SMAX: CC = ISD::SETGT; break;
9528  case ISD::SMIN: CC = ISD::SETLT; break;
9529  case ISD::UMAX: CC = ISD::SETUGT; break;
9530  case ISD::UMIN: CC = ISD::SETULT; break;
9531  }
9532 
9533  // FIXME: Should really try to split the vector in case it's legal on a
9534  // subvector.
9535  if (VT.isVector() && !isOperationLegalOrCustom(ISD::VSELECT, VT))
9536  return DAG.UnrollVectorOp(Node);
9537 
9538  EVT BoolVT = getSetCCResultType(DAG.getDataLayout(), *DAG.getContext(), VT);
9539  SDValue Cond = DAG.getSetCC(DL, BoolVT, Op0, Op1, CC);
9540  return DAG.getSelect(DL, VT, Cond, Op0, Op1);
9541 }
9542 
9543 SDValue TargetLowering::expandAddSubSat(SDNode *Node, SelectionDAG &DAG) const {
9544  unsigned Opcode = Node->getOpcode();
9545  SDValue LHS = Node->getOperand(0);
9546  SDValue RHS = Node->getOperand(1);
9547  EVT VT = LHS.getValueType();
9548  SDLoc dl(Node);
9549 
9550  assert(VT == RHS.getValueType() && "Expected operands to be the same type");
9551  assert(VT.isInteger() && "Expected operands to be integers");
9552 
9553  // usub.sat(a, b) -> umax(a, b) - b
9554  if (Opcode == ISD::USUBSAT && isOperationLegal(ISD::UMAX, VT)) {
9555  SDValue Max = DAG.getNode(ISD::UMAX, dl, VT, LHS, RHS);
9556  return DAG.getNode(ISD::SUB, dl, VT, Max, RHS);
9557  }
9558 
9559  // uadd.sat(a, b) -> umin(a, ~b) + b
9560  if (Opcode == ISD::UADDSAT && isOperationLegal(ISD::UMIN, VT)) {
9561  SDValue InvRHS = DAG.getNOT(dl, RHS, VT);
9562  SDValue Min = DAG.getNode(ISD::UMIN, dl, VT, LHS, InvRHS);
9563  return DAG.getNode(ISD::ADD, dl, VT, Min, RHS);
9564  }
9565 
9566  unsigned OverflowOp;
9567  switch (Opcode) {
9568  case ISD::SADDSAT:
9569  OverflowOp = ISD::SADDO;
9570  break;
9571  case ISD::UADDSAT:
9572  OverflowOp = ISD::UADDO;
9573  break;
9574  case ISD::SSUBSAT:
9575  OverflowOp = ISD::SSUBO;
9576  break;
9577  case ISD::USUBSAT:
9578  OverflowOp = ISD::USUBO;
9579  break;
9580  default:
9581  llvm_unreachable("Expected method to receive signed or unsigned saturation "
9582  "addition or subtraction node.");
9583  }
9584 
9585  // FIXME: Should really try to split the vector in case it's legal on a
9586  // subvector.
9587  if (VT.isVector() && !isOperationLegalOrCustom(ISD::VSELECT, VT))
9588  return DAG.UnrollVectorOp(Node);
9589 
9590  unsigned BitWidth = LHS.getScalarValueSizeInBits();
9591  EVT BoolVT = getSetCCResultType(DAG.getDataLayout(), *DAG.getContext(), VT);
9592  SDValue Result = DAG.getNode(OverflowOp, dl, DAG.getVTList(VT, BoolVT), LHS, RHS);
9593  SDValue SumDiff = Result.getValue(0);
9594  SDValue Overflow = Result.getValue(1);
9595  SDValue Zero = DAG.getConstant(0, dl, VT);
9596  SDValue AllOnes = DAG.getAllOnesConstant(dl, VT);
9597 
9598  if (Opcode == ISD::UADDSAT) {
9599  if (getBooleanContents(VT) == ZeroOrNegativeOneBooleanContent) {
9600  // (LHS + RHS) | OverflowMask
9601  SDValue OverflowMask = DAG.getSExtOrTrunc(Overflow, dl, VT);
9602  return DAG.getNode(ISD::OR, dl, VT, SumDiff, OverflowMask);
9603  }
9604  // Overflow ? 0xffff.... : (LHS + RHS)
9605  return DAG.getSelect(dl, VT, Overflow, AllOnes, SumDiff);
9606  }
9607 
9608  if (Opcode == ISD::USUBSAT) {
9609  if (getBooleanContents(VT) == ZeroOrNegativeOneBooleanContent) {
9610  // (LHS - RHS) & ~OverflowMask
9611  SDValue OverflowMask = DAG.getSExtOrTrunc(Overflow, dl, VT);
9612  SDValue Not = DAG.getNOT(dl, OverflowMask, VT);
9613  return DAG.getNode(ISD::AND, dl, VT, SumDiff, Not);
9614  }
9615  // Overflow ? 0 : (LHS - RHS)
9616  return DAG.getSelect(dl, VT, Overflow, Zero, SumDiff);
9617  }
9618 
9619  // Overflow ? (SumDiff >> BW) ^ MinVal : SumDiff
9620  APInt MinVal = APInt::getSignedMinValue(BitWidth);
9621  SDValue SatMin = DAG.getConstant(MinVal, dl, VT);
9622  SDValue Shift = DAG.getNode(ISD::SRA, dl, VT, SumDiff,
9623  DAG.getConstant(BitWidth - 1, dl, VT));
9624  Result = DAG.getNode(ISD::XOR, dl, VT, Shift, SatMin);
9625  return DAG.getSelect(dl, VT, Overflow, Result, SumDiff);
9626 }
9627 
9628 SDValue TargetLowering::expandShlSat(SDNode *Node, SelectionDAG &DAG) const {
9629  unsigned Opcode = Node->getOpcode();
9630  bool IsSigned = Opcode == ISD::SSHLSAT;
9631  SDValue LHS = Node->getOperand(0);
9632  SDValue RHS = Node->getOperand(1);
9633  EVT VT = LHS.getValueType();
9634  SDLoc dl(Node);
9635 
9636  assert((Node->getOpcode() == ISD::SSHLSAT ||
9637  Node->getOpcode() == ISD::USHLSAT) &&
9638  "Expected a SHLSAT opcode");
9639  assert(VT == RHS.getValueType() && "Expected operands to be the same type");
9640  assert(VT.isInteger() && "Expected operands to be integers");
9641 
9642  if (VT.isVector() && !isOperationLegalOrCustom(ISD::VSELECT, VT))
9643  return DAG.UnrollVectorOp(Node);
9644 
9645  // If LHS != (LHS << RHS) >> RHS, we have overflow and must saturate.
9646 
9647  unsigned BW = VT.getScalarSizeInBits();
9648  EVT BoolVT = getSetCCResultType(DAG.getDataLayout(), *DAG.getContext(), VT);
9649  SDValue Result = DAG.getNode(ISD::SHL, dl, VT, LHS, RHS);
9650  SDValue Orig =
9651  DAG.getNode(IsSigned ? ISD::SRA : ISD::SRL, dl, VT, Result, RHS);
9652 
9653  SDValue SatVal;
9654  if (IsSigned) {
9655  SDValue SatMin = DAG.getConstant(APInt::getSignedMinValue(BW), dl, VT);
9656  SDValue SatMax = DAG.getConstant(APInt::getSignedMaxValue(BW), dl, VT);
9657  SDValue Cond =
9658  DAG.getSetCC(dl, BoolVT, LHS, DAG.getConstant(0, dl, VT), ISD::SETLT);
9659  SatVal = DAG.getSelect(dl, VT, Cond, SatMin, SatMax);
9660  } else {
9661  SatVal = DAG.getConstant(APInt::getMaxValue(BW), dl, VT);
9662  }
9663  SDValue Cond = DAG.getSetCC(dl, BoolVT, LHS, Orig, ISD::SETNE);
9664  return DAG.getSelect(dl, VT, Cond, SatVal, Result);
9665 }
9666 
9667 SDValue
9668 TargetLowering::expandFixedPointMul(SDNode *Node, SelectionDAG &DAG) const {
9669  assert((Node->getOpcode() == ISD::SMULFIX ||
9670  Node->getOpcode() == ISD::UMULFIX ||
9671  Node->getOpcode() == ISD::SMULFIXSAT ||
9672  Node->getOpcode() == ISD::UMULFIXSAT) &&
9673  "Expected a fixed point multiplication opcode");
9674 
9675  SDLoc dl(Node);
9676  SDValue LHS = Node->getOperand(0);
9677  SDValue RHS = Node->getOperand(1);
9678  EVT VT = LHS.getValueType();
9679  unsigned Scale = Node->getConstantOperandVal(2);
9680  bool Saturating = (Node->getOpcode() == ISD::SMULFIXSAT ||
9681  Node->getOpcode() == ISD::UMULFIXSAT);
9682  bool Signed = (Node->getOpcode() == ISD::SMULFIX ||
9683  Node->getOpcode() == ISD::SMULFIXSAT);
9684  EVT BoolVT = getSetCCResultType(DAG.getDataLayout(), *DAG.getContext(), VT);
9685  unsigned VTSize = VT.getScalarSizeInBits();
9686 
9687  if (!Scale) {
9688  // [us]mul.fix(a, b, 0) -> mul(a, b)
9689  if (!Saturating) {
9690  if (isOperationLegalOrCustom(ISD::MUL, VT))
9691  return DAG.getNode(ISD::MUL, dl, VT, LHS, RHS);
9692  } else if (Signed && isOperationLegalOrCustom(ISD::SMULO, VT)) {
9693  SDValue Result =
9694  DAG.getNode(ISD::SMULO, dl, DAG.getVTList(VT, BoolVT), LHS, RHS);
9695  SDValue Product = Result.getValue(0);
9696  SDValue Overflow = Result.getValue(1);
9697  SDValue Zero = DAG.getConstant(0, dl, VT);
9698 
9699  APInt MinVal = APInt::getSignedMinValue(VTSize);
9700  APInt MaxVal = APInt::getSignedMaxValue(VTSize);
9701  SDValue SatMin = DAG.getConstant(MinVal, dl, VT);
9702  SDValue SatMax = DAG.getConstant(MaxVal, dl, VT);
9703  // Xor the inputs, if resulting sign bit is 0 the product will be
9704  // positive, else negative.
9705  SDValue Xor = DAG.getNode(ISD::XOR, dl, VT, LHS, RHS);
9706  SDValue ProdNeg = DAG.getSetCC(dl, BoolVT, Xor, Zero, ISD::SETLT);
9707  Result = DAG.getSelect(dl, VT, ProdNeg, SatMin, SatMax);
9708  return DAG.getSelect(dl, VT, Overflow, Result, Product);
9709  } else if (!Signed && isOperationLegalOrCustom(ISD::UMULO, VT)) {
9710  SDValue Result =
9711  DAG.getNode(ISD::UMULO, dl, DAG.getVTList(VT, BoolVT), LHS, RHS);
9712  SDValue Product = Result.getValue(0);
9713  SDValue Overflow = Result.getValue(1);
9714 
9715  APInt MaxVal = APInt::getMaxValue(VTSize);
9716  SDValue SatMax = DAG.getConstant(MaxVal, dl, VT);
9717  return DAG.getSelect(dl, VT, Overflow, SatMax, Product);
9718  }
9719  }
9720 
9721  assert(((Signed && Scale < VTSize) || (!Signed && Scale <= VTSize)) &&
9722  "Expected scale to be less than the number of bits if signed or at "
9723  "most the number of bits if unsigned.");
9724  assert(LHS.getValueType() == RHS.getValueType() &&
9725  "Expected both operands to be the same type");
9726 
9727  // Get the upper and lower bits of the result.
9728  SDValue Lo, Hi;
9729  unsigned LoHiOp = Signed ? ISD::SMUL_LOHI : ISD::UMUL_LOHI;
9730  unsigned HiOp = Signed ? ISD::MULHS : ISD::MULHU;
9731  if (isOperationLegalOrCustom(LoHiOp, VT)) {
9732  SDValue Result = DAG.getNode(LoHiOp, dl, DAG.getVTList(VT, VT), LHS, RHS);
9733  Lo = Result.getValue(0);
9734  Hi = Result.getValue(1);
9735  } else if (isOperationLegalOrCustom(HiOp, VT)) {
9736  Lo = DAG.getNode(ISD::MUL, dl, VT, LHS, RHS);
9737  Hi = DAG.getNode(HiOp, dl, VT, LHS, RHS);
9738  } else if (VT.isVector()) {
9739  return SDValue();
9740  } else {
9741  report_fatal_error("Unable to expand fixed point multiplication.");
9742  }
9743 
9744  if (Scale == VTSize)
9745  // Result is just the top half since we'd be shifting by the width of the
9746  // operand. Overflow impossible so this works for both UMULFIX and
9747  // UMULFIXSAT.
9748  return Hi;
9749 
9750  // The result will need to be shifted right by the scale since both operands
9751  // are scaled. The result is given to us in 2 halves, so we only want part of
9752  // both in the result.
9753  EVT ShiftTy = getShiftAmountTy(VT, DAG.getDataLayout());
9754  SDValue Result = DAG.getNode(ISD::FSHR, dl, VT, Hi, Lo,
9755  DAG.getConstant(Scale, dl, ShiftTy));
9756  if (!Saturating)
9757  return Result;
9758 
9759  if (!Signed) {
9760  // Unsigned overflow happened if the upper (VTSize - Scale) bits (of the
9761  // widened multiplication) aren't all zeroes.
9762 
9763  // Saturate to max if ((Hi >> Scale) != 0),
9764  // which is the same as if (Hi > ((1 << Scale) - 1))
9765  APInt MaxVal = APInt::getMaxValue(VTSize);
9766  SDValue LowMask = DAG.getConstant(APInt::getLowBitsSet(VTSize, Scale),
9767  dl, VT);
9768  Result = DAG.getSelectCC(dl, Hi, LowMask,
9769  DAG.getConstant(MaxVal, dl, VT), Result,
9770  ISD::SETUGT);
9771 
9772  return Result;
9773  }
9774 
9775  // Signed overflow happened if the upper (VTSize - Scale + 1) bits (of the
9776  // widened multiplication) aren't all ones or all zeroes.
9777 
9778  SDValue SatMin = DAG.getConstant(APInt::getSignedMinValue(VTSize), dl, VT);
9779  SDValue SatMax = DAG.getConstant(APInt::getSignedMaxValue(VTSize), dl, VT);
9780 
9781  if (Scale == 0) {
9782  SDValue Sign = DAG.getNode(ISD::SRA, dl, VT, Lo,
9783  DAG.getConstant(VTSize - 1, dl, ShiftTy));
9784  SDValue Overflow = DAG.getSetCC(dl, BoolVT, Hi, Sign, ISD::SETNE);
9785  // Saturated to SatMin if wide product is negative, and SatMax if wide
9786  // product is positive ...
9787  SDValue Zero = DAG.getConstant(0, dl, VT);
9788  SDValue ResultIfOverflow = DAG.getSelectCC(dl, Hi, Zero, SatMin, SatMax,
9789  ISD::SETLT);
9790  // ... but only if we overflowed.
9791  return DAG.getSelect(dl, VT, Overflow, ResultIfOverflow, Result);
9792  }
9793 
9794  // We handled Scale==0 above so all the bits to examine is in Hi.
9795 
9796  // Saturate to max if ((Hi >> (Scale - 1)) > 0),
9797  // which is the same as if (Hi > (1 << (Scale - 1)) - 1)
9798  SDValue LowMask = DAG.getConstant(APInt::getLowBitsSet(VTSize, Scale - 1),
9799  dl, VT);
9800  Result = DAG.getSelectCC(dl, Hi, LowMask, SatMax, Result, ISD::SETGT);
9801  // Saturate to min if (Hi >> (Scale - 1)) < -1),
9802  // which is the same as if (HI < (-1 << (Scale - 1))
9803  SDValue HighMask =
9804  DAG.getConstant(APInt::getHighBitsSet(VTSize, VTSize - Scale + 1),
9805  dl, VT);
9806  Result = DAG.getSelectCC(dl, Hi, HighMask, SatMin, Result, ISD::SETLT);
9807  return Result;
9808 }
9809 
9810 SDValue
9811 TargetLowering::expandFixedPointDiv(unsigned Opcode, const SDLoc &dl,
9812  SDValue LHS, SDValue RHS,
9813  unsigned Scale, SelectionDAG &DAG) const {
9814  assert((Opcode == ISD::SDIVFIX || Opcode == ISD::SDIVFIXSAT ||
9815  Opcode == ISD::UDIVFIX || Opcode == ISD::UDIVFIXSAT) &&
9816  "Expected a fixed point division opcode");
9817 
9818  EVT VT = LHS.getValueType();
9819  bool Signed = Opcode == ISD::SDIVFIX || Opcode == ISD::SDIVFIXSAT;
9820  bool Saturating = Opcode == ISD::SDIVFIXSAT || Opcode == ISD::UDIVFIXSAT;
9821  EVT BoolVT = getSetCCResultType(DAG.getDataLayout(), *DAG.getContext(), VT);
9822 
9823  // If there is enough room in the type to upscale the LHS or downscale the
9824  // RHS before the division, we can perform it in this type without having to
9825  // resize. For signed operations, the LHS headroom is the number of
9826  // redundant sign bits, and for unsigned ones it is the number of zeroes.
9827  // The headroom for the RHS is the number of trailing zeroes.
9828  unsigned LHSLead = Signed ? DAG.ComputeNumSignBits(LHS) - 1
9829  : DAG.computeKnownBits(LHS).countMinLeadingZeros();
9830  unsigned RHSTrail = DAG.computeKnownBits(RHS).countMinTrailingZeros();
9831 
9832  // For signed saturating operations, we need to be able to detect true integer
9833  // division overflow; that is, when you have MIN / -EPS. However, this
9834  // is undefined behavior and if we emit divisions that could take such
9835  // values it may cause undesired behavior (arithmetic exceptions on x86, for
9836  // example).
9837  // Avoid this by requiring an extra bit so that we never get this case.
9838  // FIXME: This is a bit unfortunate as it means that for an 8-bit 7-scale
9839  // signed saturating division, we need to emit a whopping 32-bit division.
9840  if (LHSLead + RHSTrail < Scale + (unsigned)(Saturating && Signed))
9841  return SDValue();
9842 
9843  unsigned LHSShift = std::min(LHSLead, Scale);
9844  unsigned RHSShift = Scale - LHSShift;
9845 
9846  // At this point, we know that if we shift the LHS up by LHSShift and the
9847  // RHS down by RHSShift, we can emit a regular division with a final scaling
9848  // factor of Scale.
9849 
9850  EVT ShiftTy = getShiftAmountTy(VT, DAG.getDataLayout());
9851  if (LHSShift)
9852  LHS = DAG.getNode(ISD::SHL, dl, VT, LHS,
9853  DAG.getConstant(LHSShift, dl, ShiftTy));
9854  if (RHSShift)
9855  RHS = DAG.getNode(Signed ? ISD::SRA : ISD::SRL, dl, VT, RHS,
9856  DAG.getConstant(RHSShift, dl, ShiftTy));
9857 
9858  SDValue Quot;
9859  if (Signed) {
9860  // For signed operations, if the resulting quotient is negative and the
9861  // remainder is nonzero, subtract 1 from the quotient to round towards
9862  // negative infinity.
9863  SDValue Rem;
9864  // FIXME: Ideally we would always produce an SDIVREM here, but if the
9865  // type isn't legal, SDIVREM cannot be expanded. There is no reason why
9866  // we couldn't just form a libcall, but the type legalizer doesn't do it.
9867  if (isTypeLegal(VT) &&
9868  isOperationLegalOrCustom(ISD::SDIVREM, VT)) {
9869  Quot = DAG.getNode(ISD::SDIVREM, dl,
9870  DAG.getVTList(VT, VT),
9871  LHS, RHS);
9872  Rem = Quot.getValue(1);
9873  Quot = Quot.getValue(0);
9874  } else {
9875  Quot = DAG.getNode(ISD::SDIV, dl, VT,
9876  LHS, RHS);
9877  Rem = DAG.getNode(ISD::SREM, dl, VT,
9878  LHS, RHS);
9879  }
9880  SDValue Zero = DAG.getConstant(0, dl, VT);
9881  SDValue RemNonZero = DAG.getSetCC(dl, BoolVT, Rem, Zero, ISD::SETNE);
9882  SDValue LHSNeg = DAG.getSetCC(dl, BoolVT, LHS, Zero, ISD::SETLT);
9883  SDValue RHSNeg = DAG.getSetCC(dl, BoolVT, RHS, Zero, ISD::SETLT);
9884  SDValue QuotNeg = DAG.getNode(ISD::XOR, dl, BoolVT, LHSNeg, RHSNeg);
9885  SDValue Sub1 = DAG.getNode(ISD::SUB, dl, VT, Quot,
9886  DAG.getConstant(1, dl, VT));
9887  Quot = DAG.getSelect(dl, VT,
9888  DAG.getNode(ISD::AND, dl, BoolVT, RemNonZero, QuotNeg),
9889  Sub1, Quot);
9890  } else
9891  Quot = DAG.getNode(ISD::UDIV, dl, VT,
9892  LHS, RHS);
9893 
9894  return Quot;
9895 }
9896 
9897 void TargetLowering::expandUADDSUBO(
9898  SDNode *Node, SDValue &Result, SDValue &Overflow, SelectionDAG &DAG) const {
9899  SDLoc dl(Node);
9900  SDValue LHS = Node->getOperand(0);
9901  SDValue RHS = Node->getOperand(1);
9902  bool IsAdd = Node->getOpcode() == ISD::UADDO;
9903 
9904  // If ADD/SUBCARRY is legal, use that instead.
9905  unsigned OpcCarry = IsAdd ? ISD::ADDCARRY : ISD::SUBCARRY;
9906  if (isOperationLegalOrCustom(OpcCarry, Node->getValueType(0))) {
9907  SDValue CarryIn = DAG.getConstant(0, dl, Node->getValueType(1));
9908  SDValue NodeCarry = DAG.getNode(OpcCarry, dl, Node->getVTList(),
9909  { LHS, RHS, CarryIn });
9910  Result = SDValue(NodeCarry.getNode(), 0);
9911  Overflow = SDValue(NodeCarry.getNode(), 1);
9912  return;
9913  }
9914 
9915  Result = DAG.getNode(IsAdd ? ISD::ADD : ISD::SUB, dl,
9916  LHS.getValueType(), LHS, RHS);
9917 
9918  EVT ResultType = Node->getValueType(1);
9919  EVT SetCCType = getSetCCResultType(
9920  DAG.getDataLayout(), *DAG.getContext(), Node->getValueType(0));
9921  SDValue SetCC;
9922  if (IsAdd && isOneConstant(RHS)) {
9923  // Special case: uaddo X, 1 overflowed if X+1 is 0. This potential reduces
9924  // the live range of X. We assume comparing with 0 is cheap.
9925  // The general case (X + C) < C is not necessarily beneficial. Although we
9926  // reduce the live range of X, we may introduce the materialization of
9927  // constant C.
9928  SetCC =
9929  DAG.getSetCC(dl, SetCCType, Result,
9930  DAG.getConstant(0, dl, Node->getValueType(0)), ISD::SETEQ);
9931  } else {
9932  ISD::CondCode CC = IsAdd ? ISD::SETULT : ISD::SETUGT;
9933  SetCC = DAG.getSetCC(dl, SetCCType, Result, LHS, CC);
9934  }
9935  Overflow = DAG.getBoolExtOrTrunc(SetCC, dl, ResultType, ResultType);
9936 }
9937 
9938 void TargetLowering::expandSADDSUBO(
9939  SDNode *Node, SDValue &Result, SDValue &Overflow, SelectionDAG &DAG) const {
9940  SDLoc dl(Node);
9941  SDValue LHS = Node->getOperand(0);
9942  SDValue RHS = Node->getOperand(1);
9943  bool IsAdd = Node->getOpcode() == ISD::SADDO;
9944 
9945  Result = DAG.getNode(IsAdd ? ISD::ADD : ISD::SUB, dl,
9946  LHS.getValueType(), LHS, RHS);
9947 
9948  EVT ResultType = Node->getValueType(1);
9949  EVT OType = getSetCCResultType(
9950  DAG.getDataLayout(), *DAG.getContext(), Node->getValueType(0));
9951 
9952  // If SADDSAT/SSUBSAT is legal, compare results to detect overflow.
9953  unsigned OpcSat = IsAdd ? ISD::SADDSAT : ISD::SSUBSAT;
9954  if (isOperationLegal(OpcSat, LHS.getValueType())) {
9955  SDValue Sat = DAG.getNode(OpcSat, dl, LHS.getValueType(), LHS, RHS);
9956  SDValue SetCC = DAG.getSetCC(dl, OType, Result, Sat, ISD::SETNE);
9957  Overflow = DAG.getBoolExtOrTrunc(SetCC, dl, ResultType, ResultType);
9958  return;
9959  }
9960 
9961  SDValue Zero = DAG.getConstant(0, dl, LHS.getValueType());
9962 
9963  // For an addition, the result should be less than one of the operands (LHS)
9964  // if and only if the other operand (RHS) is negative, otherwise there will
9965  // be overflow.
9966  // For a subtraction, the result should be less than one of the operands
9967  // (LHS) if and only if the other operand (RHS) is (non-zero) positive,
9968  // otherwise there will be overflow.
9969  SDValue ResultLowerThanLHS = DAG.getSetCC(dl, OType, Result, LHS, ISD::SETLT);
9970  SDValue ConditionRHS =
9971  DAG.getSetCC(dl, OType, RHS, Zero, IsAdd ? ISD::SETLT : ISD::SETGT);
9972 
9973  Overflow = DAG.getBoolExtOrTrunc(
9974  DAG.getNode(ISD::XOR, dl, OType, ConditionRHS, ResultLowerThanLHS), dl,
9975  ResultType, ResultType);
9976 }
9977 
9978 bool TargetLowering::expandMULO(SDNode *Node, SDValue &Result,
9979  SDValue &Overflow, SelectionDAG &DAG) const {
9980  SDLoc dl(Node);
9981  EVT VT = Node->getValueType(0);
9982  EVT SetCCVT = getSetCCResultType(DAG.getDataLayout(), *DAG.getContext(), VT);
9983  SDValue LHS = Node->getOperand(0);
9984  SDValue RHS = Node->getOperand(1);
9985  bool isSigned = Node->getOpcode() == ISD::SMULO;
9986 
9987  // For power-of-two multiplications we can use a simpler shift expansion.
9988  if (ConstantSDNode *RHSC = isConstOrConstSplat(RHS)) {
9989  const APInt &C = RHSC->getAPIntValue();
9990  // mulo(X, 1 << S) -> { X << S, (X << S) >> S != X }
9991  if (C.isPowerOf2()) {
9992  // smulo(x, signed_min) is same as umulo(x, signed_min).
9993  bool UseArithShift = isSigned && !C.isMinSignedValue();
9994  EVT ShiftAmtTy = getShiftAmountTy(VT, DAG.getDataLayout());
9995  SDValue ShiftAmt = DAG.getConstant(C.logBase2(), dl, ShiftAmtTy);
9996  Result = DAG.getNode(ISD::SHL, dl, VT, LHS, ShiftAmt);
9997  Overflow = DAG.getSetCC(dl, SetCCVT,
9998  DAG.getNode(UseArithShift ? ISD::SRA : ISD::SRL,
9999  dl, VT, Result, ShiftAmt),
10000  LHS, ISD::SETNE);
10001  return true;
10002  }
10003  }
10004 
10005  EVT WideVT = EVT::getIntegerVT(*DAG.getContext(), VT.getScalarSizeInBits() * 2);
10006  if (VT.isVector())
10007  WideVT =
10008  EVT::getVectorVT(*DAG.getContext(), WideVT, VT.getVectorElementCount());
10009 
10010  SDValue BottomHalf;
10011  SDValue TopHalf;
10012  static const unsigned Ops[2][3] =
10013  { { ISD::MULHU, ISD::UMUL_LOHI, ISD::ZERO_EXTEND },
10014  { ISD::MULHS, ISD::SMUL_LOHI, ISD::SIGN_EXTEND }};
10015  if (isOperationLegalOrCustom(Ops[isSigned][0], VT)) {
10016  BottomHalf = DAG.getNode(ISD::MUL, dl, VT, LHS, RHS);
10017  TopHalf = DAG.getNode(Ops[isSigned][0], dl, VT, LHS, RHS);
10018  } else if (isOperationLegalOrCustom(Ops[isSigned][1], VT)) {
10019  BottomHalf = DAG.getNode(Ops[isSigned][1], dl, DAG.getVTList(VT, VT), LHS,
10020  RHS);
10021  TopHalf = BottomHalf.getValue(1);
10022  } else if (isTypeLegal(WideVT)) {
10023  LHS = DAG.getNode(Ops[isSigned][2], dl, WideVT, LHS);
10024  RHS = DAG.getNode(Ops[isSigned][2], dl, WideVT, RHS);
10025  SDValue Mul = DAG.getNode(ISD::MUL, dl, WideVT, LHS, RHS);
10026  BottomHalf = DAG.getNode(ISD::TRUNCATE, dl, VT, Mul);
10027  SDValue ShiftAmt = DAG.getConstant(VT.getScalarSizeInBits(), dl,
10028  getShiftAmountTy(WideVT, DAG.getDataLayout()));
10029  TopHalf = DAG.getNode(ISD::TRUNCATE, dl, VT,
10030  DAG.getNode(ISD::SRL, dl, WideVT, Mul, ShiftAmt));
10031  } else {
10032  if (VT.isVector())
10033  return false;
10034 
10035  // We can fall back to a libcall with an illegal type for the MUL if we
10036  // have a libcall big enough.
10037  // Also, we can fall back to a division in some cases, but that's a big
10038  // performance hit in the general case.
10039  RTLIB::Libcall LC = RTLIB::UNKNOWN_LIBCALL;
10040  if (WideVT == MVT::i16)
10041  LC = RTLIB::MUL_I16;
10042  else if (WideVT == MVT::i32)
10043  LC = RTLIB::MUL_I32;
10044  else if (WideVT == MVT::i64)
10045  LC = RTLIB::MUL_I64;
10046  else if (WideVT == MVT::i128)
10047  LC = RTLIB::MUL_I128;
10048  assert(LC != RTLIB::UNKNOWN_LIBCALL && "Cannot expand this operation!");
10049 
10050  SDValue HiLHS;
10051  SDValue HiRHS;
10052  if (isSigned) {
10053  // The high part is obtained by SRA'ing all but one of the bits of low
10054  // part.
10055  unsigned LoSize = VT.getFixedSizeInBits();
10056  HiLHS =
10057  DAG.getNode(ISD::SRA, dl, VT, LHS,
10058  DAG.getConstant(LoSize - 1, dl,
10059  getPointerTy(DAG.getDataLayout())));
10060  HiRHS =
10061  DAG.getNode(ISD::SRA, dl, VT, RHS,
10062  DAG.getConstant(LoSize - 1, dl,
10063  getPointerTy(DAG.getDataLayout())));
10064  } else {
10065  HiLHS = DAG.getConstant(0, dl, VT);
10066  HiRHS = DAG.getConstant(0, dl, VT);
10067  }
10068 
10069  // Here we're passing the 2 arguments explicitly as 4 arguments that are
10070  // pre-lowered to the correct types. This all depends upon WideVT not
10071  // being a legal type for the architecture and thus has to be split to
10072  // two arguments.
10073  SDValue Ret;
10074  TargetLowering::MakeLibCallOptions CallOptions;
10075  CallOptions.setSExt(isSigned);
10076  CallOptions.setIsPostTypeLegalization(true);
10077  if (shouldSplitFunctionArgumentsAsLittleEndian(DAG.getDataLayout())) {
10078  // Halves of WideVT are packed into registers in different order
10079  // depending on platform endianness. This is usually handled by
10080  // the C calling convention, but we can't defer to it in
10081  // the legalizer.
10082  SDValue Args[] = { LHS, HiLHS, RHS, HiRHS };
10083  Ret = makeLibCall(DAG, LC, WideVT, Args, CallOptions, dl).first;
10084  } else {
10085  SDValue Args[] = { HiLHS, LHS, HiRHS, RHS };
10086  Ret = makeLibCall(DAG, LC, WideVT, Args, CallOptions, dl).first;
10087  }
10088  assert(Ret.getOpcode() == ISD::MERGE_VALUES &&
10089  "Ret value is a collection of constituent nodes holding result.");
10090  if (DAG.getDataLayout().isLittleEndian()) {
10091  // Same as above.
10092  BottomHalf = Ret.getOperand(0);
10093  TopHalf = Ret.getOperand(1);
10094  } else {
10095  BottomHalf = Ret.getOperand(1);
10096  TopHalf = Ret.getOperand(0);
10097  }
10098  }
10099 
10100  Result = BottomHalf;
10101  if (isSigned) {
10102  SDValue ShiftAmt = DAG.getConstant(
10103  VT.getScalarSizeInBits() - 1, dl,
10104  getShiftAmountTy(BottomHalf.getValueType(), DAG.getDataLayout()));
10105  SDValue Sign = DAG.getNode(ISD::SRA, dl, VT, BottomHalf, ShiftAmt);
10106  Overflow = DAG.getSetCC(dl, SetCCVT, TopHalf, Sign, ISD::SETNE);
10107  } else {
10108  Overflow = DAG.getSetCC(dl, SetCCVT, TopHalf,
10109  DAG.getConstant(0, dl, VT), ISD::SETNE);
10110  }
10111 
10112  // Truncate the result if SetCC returns a larger type than needed.
10113  EVT RType = Node->getValueType(1);
10114  if (RType.bitsLT(Overflow.getValueType()))
10115  Overflow = DAG.getNode(ISD::TRUNCATE, dl, RType, Overflow);
10116 
10117  assert(RType.getSizeInBits() == Overflow.getValueSizeInBits() &&
10118  "Unexpected result type for S/UMULO legalization");
10119  return true;
10120 }
10121 
10122 SDValue TargetLowering::expandVecReduce(SDNode *Node, SelectionDAG &DAG) const {
10123  SDLoc dl(Node);
10124  unsigned BaseOpcode = ISD::getVecReduceBaseOpcode(Node->getOpcode());
10125  SDValue Op = Node->getOperand(0);
10126  EVT VT = Op.getValueType();
10127 
10128  if (VT.isScalableVector())
10129  report_fatal_error(
10130  "Expanding reductions for scalable vectors is undefined.");
10131 
10132  // Try to use a shuffle reduction for power of two vectors.
10133  if (VT.isPow2VectorType()) {
10134  while (VT.getVectorNumElements() > 1) {
10135  EVT HalfVT = VT.getHalfNumVectorElementsVT(*DAG.getContext());
10136  if (!isOperationLegalOrCustom(BaseOpcode, HalfVT))
10137  break;
10138 
10139  SDValue Lo, Hi;
10140  std::tie(Lo, Hi) = DAG.SplitVector(Op, dl);
10141  Op = DAG.getNode(BaseOpcode, dl, HalfVT, Lo, Hi);
10142  VT = HalfVT;
10143  }
10144  }
10145 
10146  EVT EltVT = VT.getVectorElementType();
10147  unsigned NumElts = VT.getVectorNumElements();
10148 
10149  SmallVector<SDValue, 8> Ops;
10150  DAG.ExtractVectorElements(Op, Ops, 0, NumElts);
10151 
10152  SDValue Res = Ops[0];
10153  for (unsigned i = 1; i < NumElts; i++)
10154  Res = DAG.getNode(BaseOpcode, dl, EltVT, Res, Ops[i], Node->getFlags());
10155 
10156  // Result type may be wider than element type.
10157  if (EltVT != Node->getValueType(0))
10158  Res = DAG.getNode(ISD::ANY_EXTEND, dl, Node->getValueType(0), Res);
10159  return Res;
10160 }
10161 
10162 SDValue TargetLowering::expandVecReduceSeq(SDNode *Node, SelectionDAG &DAG) const {
10163  SDLoc dl(Node);
10164  SDValue AccOp = Node->getOperand(0);
10165  SDValue VecOp = Node->getOperand(1);
10166  SDNodeFlags Flags = Node->getFlags();
10167 
10168  EVT VT = VecOp.getValueType();
10169  EVT EltVT = VT.getVectorElementType();
10170 
10171  if (VT.isScalableVector())
10172  report_fatal_error(
10173  "Expanding reductions for scalable vectors is undefined.");
10174 
10175  unsigned NumElts = VT.getVectorNumElements();
10176 
10177  SmallVector<SDValue, 8> Ops;
10178  DAG.ExtractVectorElements(VecOp, Ops, 0, NumElts);
10179 
10180  unsigned BaseOpcode = ISD::getVecReduceBaseOpcode(Node->getOpcode());
10181 
10182  SDValue Res = AccOp;
10183  for (unsigned i = 0; i < NumElts; i++)
10184  Res = DAG.getNode(BaseOpcode, dl, EltVT, Res, Ops[i], Flags);
10185 
10186  return Res;
10187 }
10188 
10189 bool TargetLowering::expandREM(SDNode *Node, SDValue &Result,
10190  SelectionDAG &DAG) const {
10191  EVT VT = Node->getValueType(0);
10192  SDLoc dl(Node);
10193  bool isSigned = Node->getOpcode() == ISD::SREM;
10194  unsigned DivOpc = isSigned ? ISD::SDIV : ISD::UDIV;
10195  unsigned DivRemOpc = isSigned ? ISD::SDIVREM : ISD::UDIVREM;
10196  SDValue Dividend = Node->getOperand(0);
10197  SDValue Divisor = Node->getOperand(1);
10198  if (isOperationLegalOrCustom(DivRemOpc, VT)) {
10199  SDVTList VTs = DAG.getVTList(VT, VT);
10200  Result = DAG.getNode(DivRemOpc, dl, VTs, Dividend, Divisor).getValue(1);
10201  return true;
10202  }
10203  if (isOperationLegalOrCustom(DivOpc, VT)) {
10204  // X % Y -> X-X/Y*Y
10205  SDValue Divide = DAG.getNode(DivOpc, dl, VT, Dividend, Divisor);
10206  SDValue Mul = DAG.getNode(ISD::MUL, dl, VT, Divide, Divisor);
10207  Result = DAG.getNode(ISD::SUB, dl, VT, Dividend, Mul);
10208  return true;
10209  }
10210  return false;
10211 }
10212 
10213 SDValue TargetLowering::expandFP_TO_INT_SAT(SDNode *Node,
10214  SelectionDAG &DAG) const {
10215  bool IsSigned = Node->getOpcode() == ISD::FP_TO_SINT_SAT;
10216  SDLoc dl(SDValue(Node, 0));
10217  SDValue Src = Node->getOperand(0);
10218 
10219  // DstVT is the result type, while SatVT is the size to which we saturate
10220  EVT SrcVT = Src.getValueType();
10221  EVT DstVT = Node->getValueType(0);
10222 
10223  EVT SatVT = cast<VTSDNode>(Node->getOperand(1))->getVT();
10224  unsigned SatWidth = SatVT.getScalarSizeInBits();
10225  unsigned DstWidth = DstVT.getScalarSizeInBits();
10226  assert(SatWidth <= DstWidth &&
10227  "Expected saturation width smaller than result width");
10228 
10229  // Determine minimum and maximum integer values and their corresponding
10230  // floating-point values.
10231  APInt MinInt, MaxInt;
10232  if (IsSigned) {
10233  MinInt = APInt::getSignedMinValue(SatWidth).sext(DstWidth);
10234  MaxInt = APInt::getSignedMaxValue(SatWidth).sext(DstWidth);
10235  } else {
10236  MinInt = APInt::getMinValue(SatWidth).zext(DstWidth);
10237  MaxInt = APInt::getMaxValue(SatWidth).zext(DstWidth);
10238  }
10239 
10240  // We cannot risk emitting FP_TO_XINT nodes with a source VT of f16, as
10241  // libcall emission cannot handle this. Large result types will fail.
10242  if (SrcVT == MVT::f16) {
10243  Src = DAG.getNode(ISD::FP_EXTEND, dl, MVT::f32, Src);
10244  SrcVT = Src.getValueType();
10245  }
10246 
10247  APFloat MinFloat(DAG.EVTToAPFloatSemantics(SrcVT));
10248  APFloat MaxFloat(DAG.EVTToAPFloatSemantics(SrcVT));
10249 
10250  APFloat::opStatus MinStatus =
10251  MinFloat.convertFromAPInt(MinInt, IsSigned, APFloat::rmTowardZero);
10252  APFloat::opStatus MaxStatus =
10253  MaxFloat.convertFromAPInt(MaxInt, IsSigned, APFloat::rmTowardZero);
10254  bool AreExactFloatBounds = !(MinStatus & APFloat::opStatus::opInexact) &&
10255  !(MaxStatus & APFloat::opStatus::opInexact);
10256 
10257  SDValue MinFloatNode = DAG.getConstantFP(MinFloat, dl, SrcVT);
10258  SDValue MaxFloatNode = DAG.getConstantFP(MaxFloat, dl, SrcVT);
10259 
10260  // If the integer bounds are exactly representable as floats and min/max are
10261  // legal, emit a min+max+fptoi sequence. Otherwise we have to use a sequence
10262  // of comparisons and selects.
10263  bool MinMaxLegal = isOperationLegal(ISD::FMINNUM, SrcVT) &&
10264  isOperationLegal(ISD::FMAXNUM, SrcVT);
10265  if (AreExactFloatBounds && MinMaxLegal) {
10266  SDValue Clamped = Src;
10267 
10268  // Clamp Src by MinFloat from below. If Src is NaN the result is MinFloat.
10269  Clamped = DAG.getNode(ISD::FMAXNUM, dl, SrcVT, Clamped, MinFloatNode);
10270  // Clamp by MaxFloat from above. NaN cannot occur.
10271  Clamped = DAG.getNode(ISD::FMINNUM, dl, SrcVT, Clamped, MaxFloatNode);
10272  // Convert clamped value to integer.
10273  SDValue FpToInt = DAG.getNode(IsSigned ? ISD::FP_TO_SINT : ISD::FP_TO_UINT,
10274  dl, DstVT, Clamped);
10275 
10276  // In the unsigned case we're done, because we mapped NaN to MinFloat,
10277  // which will cast to zero.
10278  if (!IsSigned)
10279  return FpToInt;
10280 
10281  // Otherwise, select 0 if Src is NaN.
10282  SDValue ZeroInt = DAG.getConstant(0, dl, DstVT);
10283  return DAG.getSelectCC(dl, Src, Src, ZeroInt, FpToInt,
10284  ISD::CondCode::SETUO);
10285  }
10286 
10287  SDValue MinIntNode = DAG.getConstant(MinInt, dl, DstVT);
10288  SDValue MaxIntNode = DAG.getConstant(MaxInt, dl, DstVT);
10289 
10290  // Result of direct conversion. The assumption here is that the operation is
10291  // non-trapping and it's fine to apply it to an out-of-range value if we
10292  // select it away later.
10293  SDValue FpToInt =
10294  DAG.getNode(IsSigned ? ISD::FP_TO_SINT : ISD::FP_TO_UINT, dl, DstVT, Src);
10295 
10296  SDValue Select = FpToInt;
10297 
10298  // If Src ULT MinFloat, select MinInt. In particular, this also selects
10299  // MinInt if Src is NaN.
10300  Select = DAG.getSelectCC(dl, Src, MinFloatNode, MinIntNode, Select,
10301  ISD::CondCode::SETULT);
10302  // If Src OGT MaxFloat, select MaxInt.
10303  Select = DAG.getSelectCC(dl, Src, MaxFloatNode, MaxIntNode, Select,
10304  ISD::CondCode::SETOGT);
10305 
10306  // In the unsigned case we are done, because we mapped NaN to MinInt, which
10307  // is already zero.
10308  if (!IsSigned)
10309  return Select;
10310 
10311  // Otherwise, select 0 if Src is NaN.
10312  SDValue ZeroInt = DAG.getConstant(0, dl, DstVT);
10313  return DAG.getSelectCC(dl, Src, Src, ZeroInt, Select, ISD::CondCode::SETUO);
10314 }
10315 
10316 SDValue TargetLowering::expandVectorSplice(SDNode *Node,
10317  SelectionDAG &DAG) const {
10318  assert(Node->getOpcode() == ISD::VECTOR_SPLICE && "Unexpected opcode!");
10319  assert(Node->getValueType(0).isScalableVector() &&
10320  "Fixed length vector types expected to use SHUFFLE_VECTOR!");
10321 
10322  EVT VT = Node->getValueType(0);
10323  SDValue V1 = Node->getOperand(0);
10324  SDValue V2 = Node->getOperand(1);
10325  int64_t Imm = cast<ConstantSDNode>(Node->getOperand(2))->getSExtValue();
10326  SDLoc DL(Node);
10327 
10328  // Expand through memory thusly:
10329  // Alloca CONCAT_VECTORS_TYPES(V1, V2) Ptr
10330  // Store V1, Ptr
10331  // Store V2, Ptr + sizeof(V1)
10332  // If (Imm < 0)
10333  // TrailingElts = -Imm
10334  // Ptr = Ptr + sizeof(V1) - (TrailingElts * sizeof(VT.Elt))
10335  // else
10336  // Ptr = Ptr + (Imm * sizeof(VT.Elt))
10337  // Res = Load Ptr
10338 
10339  Align Alignment = DAG.getReducedAlign(VT, /*UseABI=*/false);
10340 
10341  EVT MemVT = EVT::getVectorVT(*DAG.getContext(), VT.getVectorElementType(),
10342  VT.getVectorElementCount() * 2);
10343  SDValue StackPtr = DAG.CreateStackTemporary(MemVT.getStoreSize(), Alignment);
10344  EVT PtrVT = StackPtr.getValueType();
10345  auto &MF = DAG.getMachineFunction();
10346  auto FrameIndex = cast<FrameIndexSDNode>(StackPtr.getNode())->getIndex();
10347  auto PtrInfo = MachinePointerInfo::getFixedStack(MF, FrameIndex);
10348 
10349  // Store the lo part of CONCAT_VECTORS(V1, V2)
10350  SDValue StoreV1 = DAG.getStore(DAG.getEntryNode(), DL, V1, StackPtr, PtrInfo);
10351  // Store the hi part of CONCAT_VECTORS(V1, V2)
10352  SDValue OffsetToV2 = DAG.getVScale(
10353  DL, PtrVT,
10354  APInt(PtrVT.getFixedSizeInBits(), VT.getStoreSize().getKnownMinValue()));
10355  SDValue StackPtr2 = DAG.getNode(ISD::ADD, DL, PtrVT, StackPtr, OffsetToV2);
10356  SDValue StoreV2 = DAG.getStore(StoreV1, DL, V2, StackPtr2, PtrInfo);
10357 
10358  if (Imm >= 0) {
10359  // Load back the required element. getVectorElementPointer takes care of
10360  // clamping the index if it's out-of-bounds.
10361  StackPtr = getVectorElementPointer(DAG, StackPtr, VT, Node->getOperand(2));
10362  // Load the spliced result
10363  return DAG.getLoad(VT, DL, StoreV2, StackPtr,
10364  MachinePointerInfo::getUnknownStack(MF));
10365  }
10366 
10367  uint64_t TrailingElts = -Imm;
10368 
10369  // NOTE: TrailingElts must be clamped so as not to read outside of V1:V2.
10370  TypeSize EltByteSize = VT.getVectorElementType().getStoreSize();
10371  SDValue TrailingBytes =
10372  DAG.getConstant(TrailingElts * EltByteSize, DL, PtrVT);
10373 
10374  if (TrailingElts > VT.getVectorMinNumElements()) {
10375  SDValue VLBytes =
10376  DAG.getVScale(DL, PtrVT,
10377  APInt(PtrVT.getFixedSizeInBits(),
10378  VT.getStoreSize().getKnownMinValue()));
10379  TrailingBytes = DAG.getNode(ISD::UMIN, DL, PtrVT, TrailingBytes, VLBytes);
10380  }
10381 
10382  // Calculate the start address of the spliced result.
10383  StackPtr2 = DAG.getNode(ISD::SUB, DL, PtrVT, StackPtr2, TrailingBytes);
10384 
10385  // Load the spliced result
10386  return DAG.getLoad(VT, DL, StoreV2, StackPtr2,
10387  MachinePointerInfo::getUnknownStack(MF));
10388 }
10389 
10390 bool TargetLowering::LegalizeSetCCCondCode(SelectionDAG &DAG, EVT VT,
10391  SDValue &LHS, SDValue &RHS,
10392  SDValue &CC, SDValue Mask,
10393  SDValue EVL, bool &NeedInvert,
10394  const SDLoc &dl, SDValue &Chain,
10395  bool IsSignaling) const {
10396  const TargetLowering &TLI = DAG.getTargetLoweringInfo();
10397  MVT OpVT = LHS.getSimpleValueType();
10398  ISD::CondCode CCCode = cast<CondCodeSDNode>(CC)->get();
10399  NeedInvert = false;
10400  assert(!EVL == !Mask && "VP Mask and EVL must either both be set or unset");
10401  bool IsNonVP = !EVL;
10402  switch (TLI.getCondCodeAction(CCCode, OpVT)) {
10403  default:
10404  llvm_unreachable("Unknown condition code action!");
10405  case TargetLowering::Legal:
10406  // Nothing to do.
10407  break;
10408  case TargetLowering::Expand: {
10409  ISD::CondCode InvCC = ISD::getSetCCSwappedOperands(CCCode);
10410  if (TLI.isCondCodeLegalOrCustom(InvCC, OpVT)) {
10411  std::swap(LHS, RHS);
10412  CC = DAG.getCondCode(InvCC);
10413  return true;
10414  }
10415  // Swapping operands didn't work. Try inverting the condition.
10416  bool NeedSwap = false;
10417  InvCC = getSetCCInverse(CCCode, OpVT);
10418  if (!TLI.isCondCodeLegalOrCustom(InvCC, OpVT)) {
10419  // If inverting the condition is not enough, try swapping operands
10420  // on top of it.
10421  InvCC = ISD::getSetCCSwappedOperands(InvCC);
10422  NeedSwap = true;
10423  }
10424  if (TLI.isCondCodeLegalOrCustom(InvCC, OpVT)) {
10425  CC = DAG.getCondCode(InvCC);
10426  NeedInvert = true;
10427  if (NeedSwap)
10428  std::swap(LHS, RHS);
10429  return true;
10430  }
10431 
10432  ISD::CondCode CC1 = ISD::SETCC_INVALID, CC2 = ISD::SETCC_INVALID;
10433  unsigned Opc = 0;
10434  switch (CCCode) {
10435  default:
10436  llvm_unreachable("Don't know how to expand this condition!");
10437  case ISD::SETUO:
10438  if (TLI.isCondCodeLegal(ISD::SETUNE, OpVT)) {
10439  CC1 = ISD::SETUNE;
10440  CC2 = ISD::SETUNE;
10441  Opc = ISD::OR;
10442  break;
10443  }
10444  assert(TLI.isCondCodeLegal(ISD::SETOEQ, OpVT) &&
10445  "If SETUE is expanded, SETOEQ or SETUNE must be legal!");
10446  NeedInvert = true;
10447  [[fallthrough]];
10448  case ISD::SETO:
10449  assert(TLI.isCondCodeLegal(ISD::SETOEQ, OpVT) &&
10450  "If SETO is expanded, SETOEQ must be legal!");
10451  CC1 = ISD::SETOEQ;
10452  CC2 = ISD::SETOEQ;
10453  Opc = ISD::AND;
10454  break;
10455  case ISD::SETONE:
10456  case ISD::SETUEQ:
10457  // If the SETUO or SETO CC isn't legal, we might be able to use
10458  // SETOGT || SETOLT, inverting the result for SETUEQ. We only need one
10459  // of SETOGT/SETOLT to be legal, the other can be emulated by swapping
10460  // the operands.
10461  CC2 = ((unsigned)CCCode & 0x8U) ? ISD::SETUO : ISD::SETO;
10462  if (!TLI.isCondCodeLegal(CC2, OpVT) &&
10463  (TLI.isCondCodeLegal(ISD::SETOGT, OpVT) ||
10464  TLI.isCondCodeLegal(ISD::SETOLT, OpVT))) {
10465  CC1 = ISD::SETOGT;
10466  CC2 = ISD::SETOLT;
10467  Opc = ISD::OR;
10468  NeedInvert = ((unsigned)CCCode & 0x8U);
10469  break;
10470  }
10471  [[fallthrough]];
10472  case ISD::SETOEQ:
10473  case ISD::SETOGT:
10474  case ISD::SETOGE:
10475  case ISD::SETOLT:
10476  case ISD::SETOLE:
10477  case ISD::SETUNE:
10478  case ISD::SETUGT:
10479  case ISD::SETUGE:
10480  case ISD::SETULT:
10481  case ISD::SETULE:
10482  // If we are floating point, assign and break, otherwise fall through.
10483  if (!OpVT.isInteger()) {
10484  // We can use the 4th bit to tell if we are the unordered
10485  // or ordered version of the opcode.
10486  CC2 = ((unsigned)CCCode & 0x8U) ? ISD::SETUO : ISD::SETO;
10487  Opc = ((unsigned)CCCode & 0x8U) ? ISD::OR : ISD::AND;
10488  CC1 = (ISD::CondCode)(((int)CCCode & 0x7) | 0x10);
10489  break;
10490  }
10491  // Fallthrough if we are unsigned integer.
10492  [[fallthrough]];
10493  case ISD::SETLE:
10494  case ISD::SETGT:
10495  case ISD::SETGE:
10496  case ISD::SETLT:
10497  case ISD::SETNE:
10498  case ISD::SETEQ:
10499  // If all combinations of inverting the condition and swapping operands
10500  // didn't work then we have no means to expand the condition.
10501  llvm_unreachable("Don't know how to expand this condition!");
10502  }
10503 
10504  SDValue SetCC1, SetCC2;
10505  if (CCCode != ISD::SETO && CCCode != ISD::SETUO) {
10506  // If we aren't the ordered or unorder operation,
10507  // then the pattern is (LHS CC1 RHS) Opc (LHS CC2 RHS).
10508  if (IsNonVP) {
10509  SetCC1 = DAG.getSetCC(dl, VT, LHS, RHS, CC1, Chain, IsSignaling);
10510  SetCC2 = DAG.getSetCC(dl, VT, LHS, RHS, CC2, Chain, IsSignaling);
10511  } else {
10512  SetCC1 = DAG.getSetCCVP(dl, VT, LHS, RHS, CC1, Mask, EVL);
10513  SetCC2 = DAG.getSetCCVP(dl, VT, LHS, RHS, CC2, Mask, EVL);
10514  }
10515  } else {
10516  // Otherwise, the pattern is (LHS CC1 LHS) Opc (RHS CC2 RHS)
10517  if (IsNonVP) {
10518  SetCC1 = DAG.getSetCC(dl, VT, LHS, LHS, CC1, Chain, IsSignaling);
10519  SetCC2 = DAG.getSetCC(dl, VT, RHS, RHS, CC2, Chain, IsSignaling);
10520  } else {
10521  SetCC1 = DAG.getSetCCVP(dl, VT, LHS, LHS, CC1, Mask, EVL);
10522  SetCC2 = DAG.getSetCCVP(dl, VT, RHS, RHS, CC2, Mask, EVL);
10523  }
10524  }
10525  if (Chain)
10526  Chain = DAG.getNode(ISD::TokenFactor, dl, MVT::Other, SetCC1.getValue(1),
10527  SetCC2.getValue(1));
10528  if (IsNonVP)
10529  LHS = DAG.getNode(Opc, dl, VT, SetCC1, SetCC2);
10530  else {
10531  // Transform the binary opcode to the VP equivalent.
10532  assert((Opc == ISD::OR || Opc == ISD::AND) && "Unexpected opcode");
10533  Opc = Opc == ISD::OR ? ISD::VP_OR : ISD::VP_AND;
10534  LHS = DAG.getNode(Opc, dl, VT, SetCC1, SetCC2, Mask, EVL);
10535  }
10536  RHS = SDValue();
10537  CC = SDValue();
10538  return true;
10539  }
10540  }
10541  return false;
10542 }
